\h Mark
\toc1 Mark
\toc2 Mark
\toc3 Mrk
\mt2 The account of Yeshua's ministry by
\mt1 Mark
\is1 Introduction
\is2 Author
\ip This account about the works and teachings of Yeshua was written by Mark, the son of a Jewish family who lived in Yerushalem. His mother was named Maria (Acts 12:12).
\ip Many people think he was Yohan Mark, a cousin of Barnabas (Col. 4:10) who accompanied Paul on his first long-distance trip to spread the good message about Yeshua the messiah (Acts 12:25, 13:13). We also know that Mark accompanied Peter (1 Peter 5:13), and some consider that it might have been Peter who narrated to Mark what Yeshua had done and taught.
\is2 This account
\ip This account seems to have been written for non-Jews, especially perhaps those familiar with Roman customs. So he didn't use as much ink as Matthew or Luke explaining prophecies from the Jewish scriptures but he does however, take time to explain Jewish customs to help non-Jewish readers.
\ip Mark explains here that Yeshua came to serve both God and the people, and he often refers to him as вҖҳhumanity's childвҖҷ (traditionally translated very literally from the Greek as the вҖҳSon of ManвҖҷ). We can see that especially in 10:45: вҖңEven humanity's child didn't come to be served, but to serve others and to give his life as a ransom to set many people free.вҖқ Mark wants his readers to know that Yeshua did incredible things, but especially focuses on his teaching. He confirms the power and authority of Yeshua by telling about the miracles that he did, his healing of the sick, and his exorcism of demons.
\ip The ending of this account is often disputed, and scholars are still \jmp debating|link-href="https://textandcanon.org/a-case-for-the-longer-ending-of-mark"\jmp* about whether or not the longer ending (16:9-20) is original. The \em OET\em* includes the disputed longer ending, but displays it in a lighter colour to indicate its debatable status.
\iot Main components of Mark's account
\io1 Preparation for and arrival of the messiah \ior 1:1-13\ior*
\io1 Yeshua's activities in and around Galilee \ior 1:14вҖ“9:50\ior*
\io1 The transition from Galilee to Yerushalem \ior 10:1-52\ior*
\io1 The final week in Yerushalem \ior 11:1вҖ“15:47\ior*
\io1 Yeshua comes back to life \ior 16:1-20\ior*
\rem This is still a very early look into the unfinished text of the Open English Translation of the Bible. Please double-check the text in advance before using in public.
\ie
\c 1
\rem /s1 The Proclamation of John the Baptist; John the Baptist and Jesus; The Preaching of John the Baptist; John the Baptist Prepares the Way
\rem /r (Matthew 3.1-12; Luke 3.1-18; John 1.19-28)
\m
\v 1 Here beginsВҰ21569 the goodВҰ21571 messageВҰ21571 about \nd Yeshua\nd* the \nd messiahВҰ21574\nd*вҖ”the son of \nd GodВҰ21577\nd*:
\s1 The ministry of Yohan the immerser (The return of вҖҳEliyahвҖҷ)
\r (Mat. 3:1-12; Luke 3:1-18; Yhn. 1:19-28)
\p
\v 2 The prophetВҰ21589 Yeshayah wroteВҰ21582:\x + \xo 1:2: \xt Mal 3:1.\x*
\q1 вҖңSeeВҰ21590, I am sendingВҰ21592 myВҰ21596 messengerВҰ21595 to you,
\q1 the one who will be preparingВҰ21601 yourВҰ21599 pathВҰ21603.
\q1
\v 3 \x + \xo 1:3: \xt Isa 40:3 (LXX).\x*The voiceВҰ21607 \add out\add* in the wildernessВҰ21611 shoutingВҰ21608,
\q2 вҖҳGet the pathВҰ21614 ready for \nd YahwehВҰ21615\nd*;
\q2 Make it smooth for himВҰ21621 to travel on.вҖҷ вҖқ
\p
\v 4 Yohan turned up in the wildernessВҰ21703 announcingВҰ21706 that people should get immersedВҰ21700 in water in order to show that their sinsВҰ21711 have been forgivenВҰ21710.
\v 5 And many from the Yudean regionВҰ21719 and from the city of Yerushalem went out to hear him, and they confessedВҰ21735 theirВҰ21738 sinsВҰ21737 and asked Yohan to immerseВҰ21725 them in the YordanВҰ21731 riverВҰ21732.
\p
\v 6 \x + \xo 1:6: \xt 2Ki 1:8.\x*YohanВҰ21743 was dressedВҰ21744 in simple clothes made from camelВҰ21747 hairВҰ21745 with a leatherВҰ21750 beltВҰ21749 aroundВҰ21751 hisВҰ21754 waistВҰ21753, and he lived on locustsВҰ21758 and wild honeyВҰ21760.
\v 7 And he also announcedВҰ21763, вҖңThere's a greater man comingВҰ21773 soonвҖ”in fact I'm not even good enough to bendВҰ21787 down andВҰ21762 untieВҰ21788 hisВҰ21795 sandalsВҰ21793.
\v 8 I immersedВҰ21798 you in waterВҰ21801, but he will immerse you all in God's holy \nd spiritВҰ21811\nd*.вҖқ
\s1 Yeshua gets immersed and then tempted
\rem /s1 The Baptism and Temptation of Jesus
\r (Mat. 3:13вҖ“4:11; Luke 3:21-22; 4:1-13)
\p
\v 9 \fig Yeshua was immersed by Yohan.|src="41_Mk_01_06_RG.jpg" size="col" loc="1:9" copy="В© Sweet Publishing" ref="1:9"\fig*ThenВҰ21813 one day Yeshua came from \nd NazarethВҰ21826\nd* in the GalileeВҰ21828 region, andВҰ21813 he got immersed in the YordanВҰ21836 river by Yohan.
\v 10 As Yeshua came up out of the waterВҰ21846, he sawВҰ21847 the sky beingВҰ21848 opened up, andВҰ21839 God's \nd spiritВҰ21854\nd* comingВҰ21862 down on him like a doveВҰ21861.
\v 11 \x + \xo 1:11: \xt Gen 22:2; Psa 2:7; Isa 42:1; Mat 3:17; 12:18; Mrk 9:7; Luk 3:22.\x*And a voiceВҰ21870 came from the sky saying, вҖңYou are myВҰ21881 son who I love andВҰ21869 am pleasedВҰ21887 with.вҖқ
\rem /s1 The Temptation of Jesus
\p
\v 12 And thenВҰ21888 the \nd spiritВҰ21891\nd* sent himВҰ21894 into the wildernessВҰ21899
\v 13 where he was tested by SatanВҰ21913 for fortyВҰ21907 daysВҰ21908. He was out there with the wild animals, butВҰ21900 messengersВҰ21921 waited on him there.
\s1 The selection of the first followers/apprentices
\rem /s1 Proclaiming the kingdom; The Calling of the First Disciples; The Beginning of the Galilean Ministry; Jesus Calls Four Fishermen
\r (Mat. 4:12-22; Luke 4:14-15; 5:1-11)
\p
\v 14 After Yohan had been arrested, \nd Yeshua\nd* wentВҰ21932 back up to GalileeВҰ21937 announcingВҰ21938 the goodВҰ21940 news from \nd GodВҰ21944\nd*
\v 15 \x + \xo 1:15: \xt Mat 3:2.\x*sayingВҰ21946, вҖң\wj The promised timeВҰ21952 is here, and God's kingdomВҰ21957 is now near. Turn from your sins and believeВҰ21964 this goodВҰ21967 news.\wj*вҖқ
\rem /s1 Jesus Calls the First Disciples
\p
\v 16 As he went around the lake of GalileeВҰ21976, Yeshua sawВҰ21977 two fishermenВҰ21998, SimonВҰ21979 andВҰ21968 his brotherВҰ21983 AndrewВҰ21981 throwingВҰ21987 a netВҰ21987 into the lake.
\v 17 And he saidВҰ22000 to them, вҖң\wj Come with me andВҰ22007 I will make youВҰ22009 into fishermenВҰ22011 of peopleВҰ22012.\wj*вҖқ
\v 18 And so theyВҰ22020 left theirВҰ22017 fishing work andВҰ22013 went off with Yeshua.
\p
\v 19 ThenВҰ22023 a bit further on he sawВҰ22028 two of Zebedee'sВҰ22032 sons, Yacob andВҰ22023 hisВҰ22037 brotherВҰ22036 Yohan, in a boatВҰ22042 getting their netsВҰ22045 ready.
\v 20 Yeshua calledВҰ22048 them andВҰ22046 theyВҰ22067 too wentВҰ22067 off with himВҰ22070, leaving theirВҰ22055 fatherВҰ22054 ZebedeeВҰ22056 in the boatВҰ22060 with the hiredВҰ22063 workers.
\s1 Yeshua drives out a demon
\rem /s1 The Man with an Unclean Spirit; Jesus Casts Out an Evil Spirit; A Man with an Evil Spirit; Jesus Drives Out an Evil Spirit
\r (Luke 4:31-37)
\p
\v 21 They went on into CapernaumВҰ22076 where he went into the meetingВҰ22088 hallВҰ22088 andВҰ22072 began teachingВҰ22089 as soon as the rest day started.
\v 22 \x + \xo 1:22: \xt Mat 7:28-29.\x*The congregation was amazedВҰ22092 at hisВҰ22096 teaching, becauseВҰ22098 he taughtВҰ22095 with authorityВҰ22102, not like the regular teachersВҰ22108 there.
\p
\v 23 ThenВҰ22110 a demon-possessed manВҰ22118 in the meetingВҰ22115 hallВҰ22115 suddenly yelledВҰ22124 out,
\v 24 вҖңWhat are we to you, \nd Yeshua\nd* of \nd NazarethВҰ22133\nd*? You've come to destroyВҰ22136 us. I know that you'reВҰ22141 God's holy one.вҖқ
\p
\v 25 ButВҰ22148 \nd Yeshua\nd* scolded it, sayingВҰ22154, вҖң\wj Keep quietВҰ22156!\wj*вҖқ, andВҰ22148, вҖң\wj Come out of him!\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 26 ThenВҰ22165 the demonВҰ22172 threw the man into a convulsionВҰ22167, cried out loudlyВҰ22182, andВҰ22165 leftВҰ22185 him.
\v 27 Everyone was astoundedВҰ22190 and asked each other, вҖңWhat just happened? We haven't heard anything like this beforeвҖ”he has authorityВҰ22218 to commandВҰ22229 demonsВҰ22228, and they obeyВҰ22231 him!вҖқ
\p
\v 28 And the newsВҰ22237 about Yeshua spread all over the entireВҰ22242 regionВҰ22244 of GalileeВҰ22247.
\s1 Yeshua heals many others
\rem /s1 Jesus Heals Many at Simon's House
\r (Mat. 8:14-17; Luke 4:38-41)
\p
\v 29 After leaving the meetingВҰ22254 hallВҰ22254, Yeshua wentВҰ22258 into the home of SimonВҰ22262 and AndrewВҰ22264, along with Yacob and Yohan.
\v 30 Inside, Simon's mother-in-law was lyingВҰ22277 down with a feverВҰ22278, andВҰ22273 the others spoke to Yeshua aboutВҰ22283 her.
\v 31 WhenВҰ22285 he went up to her, and took hold of her handВҰ22293 and helped her up, the feverВҰ22306 left her and she prepared something for them to eat.
\p
\v 32 That eveningВҰ22312 when the sunВҰ22318 set, the people brought all those who were sickВҰ22324 or demon-possessed to Yeshua.
\v 33 It seemed like the entireВҰ22333 townВҰ22335 had gatheredВҰ22337 there outside the front doorВҰ22343.
\v 34 Yeshua healedВҰ22367 many who were sickВҰ22369 from a rangeВҰ22371 of diseasesВҰ22372, andВҰ22366 he commanded many demons to leaveвҖ”not allowingВҰ22382 them to speakВҰ22386 becauseВҰ22387 they knew that he was the \nd messiahВҰ22391\nd*.
\s1 Yeshua prays before going preaching
\rem /s1 Jesus Prays in a Solitary Place; Jesus Preaches in Galilee; A Preaching Tour in Galilee
\r (Luke 4:42-44)
\p
\v 35 In the small hours of the morning, Yeshua gotВҰ22398 upВҰ22398 and wentВҰ22401 out to a quietВҰ22404 placeВҰ22405 and prayedВҰ22409 thereВҰ22406.
\v 36 ButВҰ22411 SimonВҰ22418 andВҰ22411 the others came lookingВҰ22413 for him,
\v 37 and when they foundВҰ22425 him they saidВҰ22429, вҖңEveryone's lookingВҰ22434 forВҰ22434 you!вҖқ
\p
\v 38 And Yeshua answered, вҖң\wj Well, we'll be goingВҰ22442 into the other villagesВҰ22450 around here, so that I can also tell them. That's what I cameВҰ22467 here for.\wj*вҖқ
\v 39 \x + \xo 1:39: \xt Mat 4:23; 9:35.\x*ThenВҰ22469 he wentВҰ22470 preachingВҰ22472 in all theirВҰ22480 meetingВҰ22478 hallsВҰ22478 in GalileeВҰ22484 andВҰ22469 drivingВҰ22488 out demonsВҰ22487.
\s1 Yeshua heals a man with leprosy
\rem /s1 Jesus Cleanses a Leper; A Man With Leprosy
\r (Mat. 8:1-4; Luke 5:12-16)
\p
\v 40 A man with leprosy came to Yeshua asking him, вҖңI know that you could heal me if you wanted to.вҖқ
\p
\v 41 Yeshua felt compassionВҰ22516 for him, reached out hisВҰ22521 handВҰ22520 and touchedВҰ22522 him, and saidВҰ22525, вҖң\wj Yes, I will. Get well.\wj*вҖқ
\v 42 ThenВҰ22530 immediatelyВҰ22533 the leprosyВҰ22541 disappeared andВҰ22530 he was well again.
\v 43 SoВҰ22544 Yeshua sentВҰ22549 him away, butВҰ22544 warned him:
\v 44 \x + \xo 1:44: \xt Lev 14:1-32.\x*вҖң\wj Don't talk to anyoneВҰ22556вҖ”just go to the priestВҰ22566 and show himВҰ22554 that you're well, and as a testimonyВҰ22581 of that, make the offeringВҰ22568 that Mosheh commandedВҰ22578.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 45 ButВҰ22590 after the man left, he started telling lots of people and spreadingВҰ22591 the newsвҖ”so much so that Yeshua could no longerВҰ22595 come into the townВҰ22601 butВҰ22585 had to stay out in quieter placesВҰ22611, and people kept comingВҰ22614 to him.
\c 2
\s1 Yeshua heals a paralysed man
\rem /s1 Jesus Heals a Paralytic
\r (Mat. 9:1-8; Luke 5:17-26)
\p
\v 1 WhenВҰ22619 Yeshua came back to CapernaumВҰ22626 after a few daysВҰ22628, people soon heardВҰ22630 that he was back in the houseВҰ22634.
\v 2 And so many people turned up there thatВҰ22645 there wasn't any roomВҰ22643 leftвҖ”not even in the doorway. Inside, Yeshua was explaining the Scriptures to them.
\v 3 FourВҰ22672 men arrived, carryingВҰ22669 a paralysedВҰ22667 man to Yeshua,
\v 4 butВҰ22673 becauseВҰ22680 of the crowdВҰ22684, they were unable to get close. SoВҰ22673 they climbed up onto the flat roofВҰ22688, made a hole through itВҰ22694, andВҰ22673 loweredВҰ22695 the paralysedВҰ22705 man lyingВҰ22706 on a palletВҰ22697.
\v 5 Yeshua, observing theirВҰ22715 faithВҰ22714, saidВҰ22716 to the man, вҖң\wj Son, yourВҰ22725 sins are forgivenВҰ22722!\wj*вҖқ\f + \fr 2:5 \ft Yeshua's hearers would have taken this as a claim to be God, as they knew that only God could forgive sins.\f*
\p
\v 6 ButВҰ22737 some of the religiousВҰ22734 teachersВҰ22734 were sittingВҰ22736 thereВҰ22735, thinkingВҰ22738 to themselvesВҰ22741,
\v 7 вҖңWhy's he talkingВҰ22748 like that? He's seriously insultingВҰ22750 God. There's only one who can forgiveВҰ22753 sinsВҰ22756, and that's God himself.вҖқ
\p
\v 8 ThenВҰ22762 \nd Yeshua\nd*, knowingВҰ22764 in hisВҰ22770 spiritВҰ22769 that they are thinking like that, saidВҰ22778 to them, вҖң\wj Why are you thinking that to yourselvesВҰ22788?\wj*
\v 9 \wj WhichВҰ22790 is easierВҰ22793: to tell the paralysedВҰ22796 man that his sinsВҰ22803 have been forgivenВҰ22799, or to tell him to pick up his beddingВҰ22813 and walkВҰ22816?\wj*
\v 10 \wj But so you all can see that humanity's child \+em does\+em* have authorityВҰ22833 here on the earthВҰ22844 to forgiveВҰ22845 sinsВҰ22846,\wj*вҖқ he turned and saidВҰ22847 to the paralysedВҰ22849 manВҰ22839,
\v 11 вҖң\wj Listen. Get up, takeВҰ22856 yourВҰ22859 beddingВҰ22858, andВҰ22860 go homeВҰ22864!\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 12 SoВҰ22868 the man stood up, and picked up his beddingВҰ22879, and wentВҰ22880 out of the house where everyone sawВҰ22902 him and marvelledВҰ22886 and praisedВҰ22892 \nd GodВҰ22894\nd* sayingВҰ22896, вҖңWe'veВҰ22902 neverВҰ22901 seen anything like that happen beforeВҰ22881!вҖқ
\s1 The calling of Levi (Matthew)
\rem /s1 The Calling of Levi; Jesus Calls Levi (Matthew)
\r (Mat. 9:9-13; Luke 5:27-32)
\p
\v 13 Yeshua wentВҰ22909 out besideВҰ22912 the lakeВҰ22915 where crowdsВҰ22919 of people kept comingВҰ22920 to him andВҰ22908 he taughtВҰ22925 them.
\v 14 And as he was passingВҰ22928 by the taxВҰ22939 officeВҰ22939, he sawВҰ22929 Levi Alfaeus sittingВҰ22935 there and saidВҰ22942 to him, вҖңCome along with me.вҖқ SoВҰ22927 Levi stood up and followedВҰ22948 Yeshua.
\p
\v 15 Yeshua ended up having a meal at Levi's place, and many other taxВҰ22967 collectorsВҰ22967 and undesirablesВҰ22969 were sittingВҰ22956 there also, along with \nd Yeshua's\nd* followers, becauseВҰ22979 by thenВҰ22951, many \add people\add* were followingВҰ22983 him around.
\v 16 \add вүҲWhenВҰ22986\add* the teachersВҰ22988 from the Pharisee partyВҰ22993 noticed that Yeshua was eating beside undesirablesВҰ23005 and tax-collectors, they asked hisВҰ23015 followers, вҖңHow come he eats with tax-collectors and other low-life?вҖқ
\p
\v 17 \nd Yeshua\nd* overheard them andВҰ23034 saidВҰ23038, вҖң\wj Healthy people don'tВҰ23041 need a doctorВҰ23046вҖ”it's the sickВҰ23049 ones that do. I didn'tВҰ23041 come here to help those who think they have no needs, butВҰ23034 \+add вүЎI cameВҰ23053\+add* to call sinnersВҰ23058.\wj*вҖқ
\s1 The question of fasting
\rem /s1 Jesus Questioned About Fasting; A Discussion about Fasting
\r (Mat. 9:14-17; Luke 5:33-39)
\p
\v 18 Now the followers of Yohan-the-immerser and members of the Pharisees regularly fasted. SoВҰ23061 a small group came to Yeshua and asked, вҖңHow come Yohan's followers and the Pharisee party fast regularly, yet your followers don'tВҰ23094?вҖқ
\p
\v 19 And \nd Yeshua\nd* answered, вҖң\wj Can the friends of the groom fast when they're celebrating along with him? No, as longВҰ23116 as he's still there, they won'tВҰ23101 be fasting.\wj*
\v 20 \wj ButВҰ23139 in the future, the groom will be takenВҰ23134 away from them, andВҰ23139 \+em then\+em* they'll be fastingВҰ23141.\wj*
\p
\v 21 вҖң\wj No one sews a patch of new, unshrunkenВҰ23155 clothВҰ23154 onto an old garmentВҰ23160, because the new patch will tear away from that old fabric and itВҰ23172 will end up as a worseВҰ23181 tear.\wj*
\v 22 \wj And no one puts new wine into old wineskins, because the wine will burstВҰ23204 the \+add already stretched\+add* wineskins, and thenВҰ23187 both the wine and the wineskins will be destroyedВҰ23218. New wine mustВҰ23204 be put into \+em new\+em* wineskins.\wj*вҖқ
\s1 Working on the Rest Day
\rem /s1 The Question about the Sabbath; Pronouncement about the Sabbath; A Discussion about the Sabbath; Lord of the Sabbath
\r (Mat. 12:1-8; Luke 6:1-5)
\p
\v 23 \x + \xo 2:23: \xt Deu 23:25.\x*And it so happened that Yeshua andВҰ23232 hisВҰ23253 followers passed through some fields of grain on some daysВҰ23239 of rest. As they went through, they pluckedВҰ23258 off some headsВҰ23261 of grain.
\v 24 And some members of the Pharisee partyВҰ23265 saidВҰ23266, вҖңIt's breaking the law to harvest grain on a rest day!вҖқ
\p
\v 25 And Yeshua replied, вҖң\wj You've read yourselves what DavidВҰ23297 didВҰ23296 when himВҰ23308 andВҰ23283 his men were hungry.\wj*
\v 26 \x + \xo 2:26: \xt Lev 24:9.\x*\wj They wentВҰ23311 into God's tent and ateВҰ23329 the holy breadВҰ23325 representing the presenceВҰ23327 of God. Only the priestsВҰ23347 were allowed to eatВҰ23341 thatВҰ23337, and yet David even gaveВҰ23349 some to his men!\wj*вҖқ
\v 27 And he told the Pharisees, вҖң\wj The days of rest were created for people, not people for the rest days.\wj*
\v 28 \wj So I, humanity's child, have authority also over the dayВҰ23385 of rest.\wj*вҖқ
\c 3
\s1 The man with the curled-up hand
\rem /s1 Jesus Heals on the Sabbath; The Man with a Withered Hand; The Man with a Paralysed Hand
\r (Mat. 12:9-14; Luke 6:6-11)
\p
\v 1 And againВҰ23390 another time, Yeshua wentВҰ23387 to the meetingВҰ23393 hallВҰ23393 andВҰ23386 there was a manВҰ23399 there with a curled-up handВҰ23407.
\v 2 The religious leaders there were watchingВҰ23409 him closelyВҰ23409 to see if he would heal the man on the rest day, andВҰ23408 thenВҰ23408 if he did, they would have a case againstВҰ23423 him.
\v 3 ThenВҰ23424 Yeshua saidВҰ23425 to the manВҰ23427 with the flawed handВҰ23433, вҖң\wj Stand up there in the middle.\wj*вҖқ
\v 4 And he asked the leaders, вҖң\wj Is it allowable to do goodВҰ23460 on the rest day, or only to do evilВҰ23464? To saveВҰ23467 lifeВҰ23466, or to killВҰ23471?\wj*вҖқ ButВҰ23449 they didn't reply.
\p
\v 5 After angrily looking aroundВҰ23476 at them, grievingВҰ23481 at theirВҰ23488 complete lack of compassion, he saidВҰ23489 to the man, вҖң\wj Open up yourВҰ23495 hand!\wj*вҖқ
\v 6 The man stretched out his fingers, and his hand became totally normal. ButВҰ23509 the Pharisees quickly left, and meeting with King Herod's supportersВҰ23517, they conspired to killВҰ23528 Yeshua.
\s1 Big crowds press on Yeshua
\rem /s1 A Multitude at the Seaside; Crowds Follow Jesus; A Crowd by the Lake
\p
\v 7 After that, \nd Yeshua\nd* withdrewВҰ23538 towards the lakeВҰ23542 with hisВҰ23537 followersВҰ23551, and a hugeВҰ23544 crowdВҰ23546 of peopleВҰ23546 from the regions of both GalileeВҰ23550 and down in YudeaВҰ23557,
\v 8 along with others from Yerushalem, IdumeaВҰ23565, from across the YordanВҰ23570 River, and from up near TyreВҰ23574 and Tsidon. They cameВҰ23589 because they had heard about the amazing things he had done.
\v 9 \x + \xo 3:9-10: \xt Mrk 4:1; Luk 5:1-3.\x*SoВҰ23592 Yeshua asked hisВҰ23596 apprenticesВҰ23595 to organise a smallВҰ23598 boatВҰ23598 to be there for him so he wouldn't be cramped by the press of the crowdВҰ23604.
\v 10 Virtually anyone who had any physical issues was pressingВҰ23615 towards him to touchВҰ23622 him, becauseВҰ23611 heВҰ23612 had already healedВҰ23612 so many.
\v 11 And the demonsВҰ23633, wheneverВҰ23634 they saw Yeshua, they fell down to the ground in front of him andВҰ23628 yelled out, вҖңYou are God's son!вҖқ
\v 12 ButВҰ23657 he regularly warned them not to reveal who he was.
\s1 Yeshua appoints his twelve representatives
\rem /s1 Jesus Appoints the Twelve; The Appointing of the Twelve Apostles; Jesus Chooses the Twelve Apostles
\r (Mat. 10:1-4; Luke 6:12-16)
\p
\v 13 As Yeshua started climbing up a hillВҰ23679, he called the followers that he had selected, andВҰ23674 they wentВҰ23689 off with him.
\v 14 He appointed twelveВҰ23696 of them as his representatives so thatВҰ23698 theyВҰ23704 could stick with himВҰ23707 andВҰ23712 be sent off to be proclaimingВҰ23717 his message
\v 15 andВҰ23720 to also have authorityВҰ23724 to exorcise demonsВҰ23731.
\p
\v 16 These are the twelveВҰ23740 that he appointed: SimonВҰ23745 (butВҰ23737 he appended the nameВҰ23743 вҖңPeterВҰ23747вҖқ),
\v 17 Yacob and his brotherВҰ23758 Yohan who were Zebedee'sВҰ23753 sons (and he nicknamed them the вҖңsons of thunderВҰ23775вҖқ),
\v 18 AndrewВҰ23781, PhilipВҰ23786, BartholomewВҰ23789, MatthewВҰ23791, ThomasВҰ23794, Yacob Alfaeus, ThaddeusВҰ23804, SimonВҰ23806 from Canaan,
\v 19 andВҰ23814 YudasВҰ23815 IscariotВҰ23817 who later betrayed himВҰ23825.
\s1 The two opposing spiritual powers
\rem /s1 Jesus and Beelzebul; Jesus and Beelzebub; Jesus and the Prince of Demons
\r (Mat. 12:22-32; Luke 11:14-23; 12:10)
\p
\v 20 ThenВҰ23826 Yeshua was approaching a houseВҰ23831, butВҰ23826 the crowdВҰ23836 swarmed them againВҰ23834 so they had no opportunity to eatВҰ23845.
\v 21 The ones with him heardВҰ23848 all the noise andВҰ23846 cameВҰ23859 to get him, because they were wondering if he was crazy.
\p
\v 22 \x + \xo 3:22: \xt Mat 9:34; 10:25.\x*The religiousВҰ23872 teachersВҰ23872 had comeВҰ23876 up from Yerushalem andВҰ23870 were complaining, вҖңHe's possessed by the prince of demons. He can command them because he rules them!вҖқ
\p
\v 23 ButВҰ23897 Yeshua addressed them: вҖң\wj How could SatanВҰ23911 command himself?\wj*
\v 24 \wj If a kingdom is dividedВҰ23920 againstВҰ23918 itselfВҰ23919, that kingdom could never prosper.\wj*
\v 25 \wj If a household is dividedВҰ23933 againstВҰ23931 itselfВҰ23932, that family will never prosper.\wj*
\v 26 \wj SoВҰ23944 if SatanВҰ23948 attacked himselfВҰ23954 andВҰ23944 was split, he couldn't possibly be powerful, butВҰ23944 his time would be over.\wj*
\p
\v 27 \wj On the contrary, no one can enter a strong man's house to clean out hisВҰ23990 possessions unless he firstВҰ23994 ties up that strong manвҖ”after that he can work on the goodsВҰ23989.\wj*
\p
\v 28 \wj Honestly, I assure youВҰ24010 that any sin of a person can be forgivenВҰ24013, no matter how much theyВҰ24031 curse God.\wj*
\v 29 \x + \xo 3:29: \xt Luk 12:10.\x*\wj But anyone who speaks againstВҰ24038 the Holy Spirit can never be forgivenВҰ24045, butВҰ24049 is eternallyВҰ24048 responsible for their sinВҰ24056.\wj*вҖқ
\v 30 (He saidВҰ24059 this becauseВҰ24058 theyВҰ24059 were sayingВҰ24059 that he was demon-possessed.)
\s1 Yeshua's mother and brothers arrive
\rem /s1 The True Family of Jesus; Jesus' Mother and Brothers; The True Kindred of Jesus
\r (Mat. 12:46-50; Luke 8:19-21)
\p
\v 31 Now Yeshua's motherВҰ24076 and brothersВҰ24080 came and were standingВҰ24084 outsideВҰ24083 and asked someone to tell him that they were there.
\v 32 Some in the crowdВҰ24101 sittingВҰ24095 aroundВҰ24097 him told Yeshua that his motherВҰ24110 andВҰ24094 brothersВҰ24114 were waiting outsideВҰ24120 for him.
\p
\v 33 ButВҰ24127 Yeshua answeredВҰ24129, вҖң\wj Who is my motherВҰ24139 andВҰ24141 who are my brothersВҰ24144?\wj*вҖқ
\v 34 And havingВҰ24147 lookedВҰ24147 around at the people sittingВҰ24154 here, he saidВҰ24157, вҖң\wj Actually, you all are my motherВҰ24162 andВҰ24146 my brothersВҰ24166.\wj*
\v 35 \wj Anyone who obeys \+nd GodВҰ24179\+nd*, that person is my brotherВҰ24182 and my sisterВҰ24185 and my motherВҰ24188.\wj*вҖқ
\c 4
\s1 The parable about planting seed
\rem /s1 Parables; Story of the Farmer Scattering Seed; The Parable of the Sower
\r (Mat. 13:1-9; Luke 8:4-8)
\p
\v 1 \x + \xo 4:1: \xt Luk 5:1-3.\x*Again Yeshua started teachingВҰ24194 by the edge of the lakeВҰ24198. A hugeВҰ24209 crowd gatheredВҰ24200 around him, butВҰ24190 he had boardedВҰ24216 a boatВҰ24215 that was floating in the water, andВҰ24190 all the people were there on the land.
\v 2 \add вүҲFrom there\add*, he taughtВҰ24246 them many different things in parablesВҰ24250, includingВҰ24253 this one:
\v 3 вҖң\wj ListenВҰ24263. Once there was a farmer who wentВҰ24264 to spread some seed.\wj*
\v 4 \wj As he spread it, some landed on the pathВҰ24281, and the birdsВҰ24287 came and fed on it.\wj*
\v 5 \wj Some landed on a rockyВҰ24302 part without a lot of soil, andВҰ24293 itВҰ24308 quickly sprouted in the warm, shallow soil,\wj*
\v 6 \wj butВҰ24327 when the sunВҰ24332 came up, it dried out becauseВҰ24336 the roots weren't deep, and so it just witheredВҰ24341 up.\wj*
\v 7 \wj Some of the seed landed in a thistle patch, and the thistles grew and chokedВҰ24357 it out, so the plants never bore a crop.\wj*
\v 8 \wj ButВҰ24365 some seed landed in fertile soil and it bore a harvestвҖ”some of it multiplying thirtyВҰ24391 times, some sixtyВҰ24397, and some a hundredВҰ24403 times.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 9 ThenВҰ24405 Yeshua added, вҖң\wj Anyone who wants to understand, let them consider it.\wj*вҖқ
\s1 Why Yeshua speaks in parables
\rem /s1 The Purpose of the Parables
\r (Mat. 13:10-17; Luke 8:9-10)
\p
\v 10 And when the crowd had left, the twelveВҰ24438 apprentices asked him aboutВҰ24433 the parablesВҰ24444.
\v 11 And he told them, вҖң\wj You've been givenВҰ24456 understanding about God's kingdomВҰ24458, butВҰ24447 for others, they'll get it in parablesВҰ24467\wj*
\q1
\v 12 \x + \xo 4:12: \xt Isa 6:9-10 (LXX).\x*\wj so that when they look they might see but not perceiveВҰ24478,\wj*
\q1 \wj and when they listen, they might hearВҰ24480 but not understandВҰ24485,\wj*
\q1 \wj otherwise they might turnВҰ24488 \+add from their sins\+add* and be forgivenВҰ24490.\wj*вҖқ
\s1 Explaining about the ground where the seed fell
\rem /s1 Jesus Explains the Parable of the Sower
\r (Mat. 13:18-23; Luke 8:11-15)
\p
\v 13 ThenВҰ24496 Yeshua saidВҰ24497 to them, вҖң\wj If you didn'tВҰ24499 understand this parableВҰ24502, how will you understand any others?\wj*
\v 14 \wj The person spreading seed is spreading the good messageВҰ24515,\wj*
\v 15 \wj and there are some alongВҰ24522 the pathВҰ24524 whereВҰ24526 the good message is beingВҰ24527 spread, who hear, butВҰ24519 SatanВҰ24538 turns up immediatelyВҰ24535 and snatches the message from them.\wj*
\v 16 \wj Similarly, there's some seed that falls onto rockyВҰ24566 placesВҰ24566 where the people who hearВҰ24572 the good messageВҰ24574 happily accept itВҰ24579,\wj*
\v 17 \wj butВҰ24580 don'tВҰ24581 make strong rootsвҖ”just temporaryВҰ24587 \+add changes\+add*. So when they get mocked or attacked about accepting the good messageВҰ24597, they quickly stumbleВҰ24600.\wj*
\v 18 \wj Others are the ones where the seed was spread amongВҰ24609 the thistles. They heardВҰ24621 the good messageВҰ24619,\wj*
\v 19 \wj butВҰ24622 contemporary topics, or the lure of money, or the appetite for otherВҰ24645 things, choke their good intentions and the messageВҰ24650 becomesВҰ24654 unfruitfulВҰ24652 in them.\wj*
\v 20 \wj ButВҰ24656 lastly, the seed that landed on the good soil represents the people who hearВҰ24671 the good messageВҰ24673, acceptВҰ24675 it, andВҰ24656 are fruitfulВҰ24677 thirtyВҰ24682, sixtyВҰ24686, or even a hundredВҰ24690 times over.\wj*вҖқ
\s1 The light will shine on everything
\rem /s1 A Lamp under a Bushel Basket; A Lamp on a Stand; A Lamp under a Bowl; Illustration of the Lamp
\r (Luke 8:16-18)
\p
\v 21 \x + \xo 4:21: \xt Mat 5:15; Luk 11:33.\x*And Yeshua told them, вҖң\wj Obviously no one goes and gets a lamp, and thenВҰ24691 puts it under a basketВҰ24706 or under the bed, butВҰ24691 rather they place it somewhere higher on a stand.\wj*
\v 22 \x + \xo 4:22: \xt Mat 10:26; Luk 12:2.\x*\wj You see, nothing is hiddenВҰ24729 that won't eventually be disclosed, andВҰ24736 there'sВҰ24727 no secretВҰ24738 that won't eventually be revealedВҰ24735.\wj*
\v 23 \wj Anyone who wants to understand must listen carefully.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 24 \x + \xo 4:24: \xt Mat 7:2; Luk 6:38.\x*And heВҰ24753 continued, вҖң\wj Take care what you listen to. Because how much you judge others, so too will judgement be handed out to you, andВҰ24752 even more.\wj*
\v 25 \x + \xo 4:25: \xt Mat 13:12; 25:29; Luk 19:26.\x*\wj Anyone who has \+add faith\+add* will be givenВҰ24776 \+add a reward\+add*, butВҰ24779 if you have none, even the little you have will be takenВҰ24786 away.\wj*вҖқ
\s1 The parable concerning the seed
\rem /s1 The Parable of the Growing Seed; Illustration of the Growing Seed
\p
\v 26 And thenВҰ24789, вҖң\wj God's kingdomВҰ24795 is like a person throwingВҰ24803 some seed onto the ground.\wj*
\v 27 \wj Whether the person sleepsВҰ24814 at night or stays up night and dayВҰ24822, the seed will sproutВҰ24826 and grow either way, and they don'tВҰ24831 know how it does it.\wj*
\v 28 \wj The earthВҰ24838 is \+add designed\+add* to multiply the seed: firstВҰ24840 a sprout appears, then a bigger plant, and then the full head of grain.\wj*
\v 29 \x + \xo 4:29: \xt Yoel 3:13.\x*\wj Then when it's ripe, the harvester is sent in becauseВҰ24865 it's ready for harvestВҰ24868.\wj*вҖқ
\s1 The small seed produces a large result
\rem /s1 Illustration of the Mustard Seed; The Parable of the Mustard Seed
\r (Mat. 13:31-32,34; Luke 13:18-19)
\p
\v 30 Again he saidВҰ24870, вҖң\wj What could we likenВҰ24874 God's kingdomВҰ24877 to? Or what parableВҰ24886 could we explain it with?\wj*
\v 31 \wj It's like planting a mustardВҰ24897 seed in the groundвҖ”a very smallВҰ24912 seed.\wj*
\v 32 \wj ButВҰ24929 when it's plantedВҰ24940 and grows up, it forms a largeВҰ24947 bush with many branchesВҰ24946 so that birdsВҰ24956 can rest in itsВҰ24954 shade.\wj*вҖқ
\rem /s1 The Use of Parables
\p
\v 33 And so as much as theyВҰ24970 could handle it, Yeshua shared the good messageВҰ24968 with them via many similar word pictures.
\v 34 He never spoke withoutВҰ24973 these illustrations, butВҰ24974 he explainedВҰ24986 all of them to his close followers.
\s1 Yeshua halts the storm on the lake
\rem /s1 Jesus Calms a Storm; Miracles; Jesus Stills a Storm
\r (Mat. 8:23-27; Luke 8:22-25)
\p
\v 35 It was already becomingВҰ24997 eveningВҰ24996 on that dayВҰ24995, so Yeshua told \add his apprentices\add*, вҖң\wj Let's all go acrossВҰ25001 to the otherВҰ25001 shoreВҰ25000.\wj*вҖқ
\v 36 SoВҰ25002 they left the crowdВҰ25007 behind andВҰ25002 got into the boatВҰ25015 with him.
\v 37 \add Out in the lake\add* a big stormВҰ25033 came up with strong winds, and the wavesВҰ25043 started breakingВҰ25046 across the boat and filling it.
\v 38 ButВҰ25057 Yeshua slept on in the backВҰ25064, sleepingВҰ25069 on a cushionВҰ25067. They woke him andВҰ25057 cried, вҖңTeacherВҰ25078, don'tВҰ25079 you care that we're all about to drown?вҖқ
\p
\v 39 Now awake, Yeshua scolded the wind and waves, вҖң\wj Quieten down! Stop that!\wj*вҖқ ThenВҰ25084 the wind died down and the water becameВҰ25105 very calm.
\v 40 And \add turning back to them\add* heВҰ25109 asked, вҖң\wj Why were you all so afraid? Don'tВҰ25116 you have any faithВҰ25121 yet?\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 41 ButВҰ25122 now they were very afraidВҰ25123 \add again\add* and asked each other, вҖңWho could this man be that both the windВҰ25139 and waves obeyВҰ25149 himВҰ25148?вҖқ
\c 5
\s1 Yeshua sends the demons into the pigs
\rem /s1 Jesus Heals a Demon-Possessed Man; Jesus Heals the Gerasene Demoniac; Jesus Heals a Man with Evil Spirits; The Healing of a Demon-possessed Man
\r (Mat. 8:28-34; Luke 8:26-39)
\p
\v 1 SoВҰ25150 theyВҰ25151 got \add safely\add* to the regionВҰ25163 of GerasenesВҰ25165 on the otherВҰ25155 sideВҰ25154 of the lakeВҰ25158.
\v 2 As Yeshua climbed out of the boatВҰ25177, a demon-possessed manВҰ25186 came out of the tombsВҰ25185 to meet him.
\v 3 He lived in those tombsВҰ25198, andВҰ25199 no one could tie himВҰ25209 up, not even with chainsВҰ25202,
\v 4 becauseВҰ25213 he had oftenВҰ25216 been tied up in the past with shackles and chains butВҰ25222 had always pulled the chains apartВҰ25229 and smashed the shackles, and no one was able to subdue him.
\v 5 All throughВҰ25255 the dayВҰ25260 and nightВҰ25257, whether in the tombsВҰ25265 or up in the hills, he was yelling out and hurting himselfВҰ25278 with stonesВҰ25280.
\p
\v 6 SoВҰ25281 when he had seenВҰ25282 \nd YeshuaВҰ25285\nd* in the distance, he ranВҰ25288 andВҰ25281 \add as a sign of honour\add* fell to the ground in front of him.
\v 7 Then he called out very loudlyВҰ25297, вҖңWhat will happen between us, \nd Yeshua\nd*, the son of the highestВҰ25310 God? I beg you in God's name not to tormentВҰ25318 me.вҖқ
\v 8 BecauseВҰ25321 Yeshua had already started sayingВҰ25320, вҖң\wj Come out of the manВҰ25334 you ungodlyВҰ25329 spiritВҰ25327!\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 9 Yeshua asked, вҖң\wj What'sВҰ25339 yourВҰ25342 name?\wj*вҖқ
\p The man answered, вҖңMy name is вҖҳThousandsвҖҷ becauseВҰ25356 there's many of us,вҖқ
\v 10 andВҰ25359 he begged Yeshua not to sendВҰ25369 them out of the countryВҰ25374.
\p
\v 11 It just so happened that thereВҰ25377 was a largeВҰ25385 herd of pigs beingВҰ25389 fed on the hillВҰ25381 nearby
\v 12 andВҰ25394 theyВҰ25395 begged Yeshua again sayingВҰ25405, вҖңSend us to the pigs so that weВҰ25416 can enter them.вҖқ
\v 13 Yeshua agreed to that, so the ungodlyВҰ25435 spiritsВҰ25433 came out of the man, wentВҰ25436 into the pigs, and the entire herd of some two thousandВҰ25454 pigs rushedВҰ25442 down the steepВҰ25447 bank into the sea and were drownedВҰ25456.
\p
\v 14 The ones who had been feedingВҰ25463 them rushed off and spread the news around in the cityВҰ25474 and the surrounding area. SoВҰ25460 the people hurried out to seeВҰ25482 what had happened.
\v 15 WhenВҰ25487 they arrived where \nd Yeshua\nd* was, they saw the man who had been demon-possessed fully-clothed and sittingВҰ25499 there in full control of his senses. They knew it was the man called вҖҳThousandsвҖҷ and they became frightened.
\v 16 Those who had seenВҰ25515 it all happen describedВҰ25511 it all to the peopleвҖ”what had happened both to the demon-possessed man andВҰ25510 to the pigs.
\p
\v 17 SoВҰ25526 thenВҰ25526 the people beganВҰ25527 asking Yeshua to goВҰ25532 away from theirВҰ25537 regionВҰ25536.
\p
\v 18 As Yeshua was climbing back into the boatВҰ25544, the man who had been demon-possessed wanted to go with him.
\p
\v 19 ButВҰ25559 Yeshua wouldn't let him and told him to head back homeВҰ25572 to his own peopleВҰ25576, and explain to them what the \nd MasterВҰ25586\nd* had doneВҰ25588 for him and how he had been merciful to him.
\p
\v 20 SoВҰ25596 he wentВҰ25597 away and shared with the people of the Ten Cities region what \nd Yeshua\nd* had done for him, and they were all amazedВҰ25613.
\s1 A woman is healed as Yeshua goes to help a dying girl
\rem /s1 A Girl Restored to Life and a Woman Healed; A Dead Girl and a Sick Woman; Jesus Heals in Response to Faith; Jairus' Daughter and the Woman Who Touched Jesus' Cloak
\r (Mat. 9:18-26; Luke 8:40-56)
\p
\v 21 WhenВҰ25614 \nd YeshuaВҰ25618\nd* had crossedВҰ25615 in the boatВҰ25621 to the otherВҰ25627 side of the lake, a largeВҰ25632 crowdВҰ25631 of people came out to the lake edge to see himВҰ25635.
\v 22 A religious leaderВҰ25647 named Jairus came out, andВҰ25641 when he found Yeshua he fell down at hisВҰ25661 feetВҰ25660
\v 23 and pleaded, вҖңMyВҰ25673 young daughterВҰ25672 is critical and just hanging on for youВҰ25681 to comeВҰ25678 and touch herВҰ25691 so that sheВҰ25694 can be healedВҰ25694 and liveВҰ25696.вҖқ
\p
\v 24 SoВҰ25698 Yeshua wentВҰ25700 off with Jairus. The largeВҰ25708 crowdВҰ25707 followedВҰ25704 also andВҰ25709 many were getting pressedВҰ25710 against Yeshua.
\p
\v 25 ThenВҰ25712 a womanВҰ25713 came who had been losing bloodВҰ25718 for twelveВҰ25720 yearsВҰ25721
\v 26 and who had endured much underВҰ25726 various doctorsВҰ25728 despite spending everything she had. After all that, she'd ended up even worseВҰ25744,
\v 27 but when she heardВҰ25747 about what Yeshua had been doing, she worked her way through the crowdВҰ25755 to the back of Yeshua and touchedВҰ25758 hisВҰ25761 clothes,
\v 28 becauseВҰ25767 sheВҰ25765 had told herself, вҖңIf I could even just touchВҰ25772 hisВҰ25780 clothesВҰ25776, I would be healedВҰ25782.вҖқ
\p
\v 29 And immediatelyВҰ25784 the bleeding stopped andВҰ25783 she knewВҰ25792 that she had been healedВҰ25796.
\v 30 Immediately also, \nd Yeshua\nd* knew that powerВҰ25813 had gone out of him, and he turnedВҰ25818 back towards the crowdВҰ25821 and saidВҰ25822, вҖң\wj Who touchedВҰ25826 myВҰ25825 clothesВҰ25828?\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 31 ButВҰ25830 hisВҰ25836 followers saidВҰ25831, вҖңYou can see all the people that were pressingВҰ25842 on you so why would you ask who touchedВҰ25849 you?вҖқ
\p
\v 32 ButВҰ25850 Yeshua was still lookingВҰ25851 aroundВҰ25851 to seeВҰ25852 who had doneВҰ25855 it.
\v 33 And the womanВҰ25860, scared and shaking because of what was happening, cameВҰ25873 and fell down in front of Yeshua and told him the whole story.
\v 34 Yeshua saidВҰ25892, вҖң\wj DaughterВҰ25895, yourВҰ25898 faithВҰ25897 has healedВҰ25899 you. Go in peaceВҰ25903 andВҰ25890 full healthВҰ25906.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 35 While he was stillВҰ25926 speakingВҰ25913, messengers came from Jairus' house to tell him, вҖңYourВҰ25923 daughterВҰ25922 has diedВҰ25924. Why bother the teacherВҰ25929 any more?вҖқ
\p
\v 36 But \nd Yeshua\nd* overheardВҰ25934 them telling this to the leaderВҰ25943 and told him, вҖң\wj Don'tВҰ25944 be afraidвҖ”keep believingВҰ25947.\wj*вҖқ
\v 37 And Yeshua didn'tВҰ25949 allowВҰ25950 anyoneВҰ25951 to accompanyВҰ25961 himВҰ25956 other than PeterВҰ25966, and Yacob and his brotherВҰ25972, Yohan.
\v 38 As theyВҰ25976 approached Jairus' houseВҰ25981, Yeshua saw a big commotionВҰ25988 with lots of crying andВҰ25975 yelling going on.
\v 39 As he entered, he saidВҰ25999, вҖң\wj Why are you all crying in distressВҰ26002? The childВҰ26007 hasn't diedВҰ26009вҖ”she's just sleepingВҰ26011!\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 40 ButВҰ26014 they just ridiculedВҰ26015 Yeshua. SoВҰ26014 he sent them all outside, just takingВҰ26029 the fatherВҰ26031 andВҰ26014 motherВҰ26039 of the child, along with three with him. He went in whereВҰ26050 the girl was
\v 41 andВҰ26056 taking her handВҰ26060, he saidВҰ26064, вҖң\wj Young woman, I tell you: get up!\wj*вҖқ
\v 42 Immediately she got up andВҰ26080 walked around. And everyone marvelledВҰ26094 at the amazing thing that had happened. (She was twelveВҰ26092 yearsВҰ26091 old.)
\v 43 Yeshua repeatedly told them to keep this to themselves, andВҰ26107 added that they should give herВҰ26111 somethingВҰ26111 to eatВҰ26112.
\c 6
\s1 Yeshua's community can't believe he's from God
\rem /s1 Jesus Is Rejected at Nazareth; A Prophet Without Honour; The Rejection of Jesus at Nazareth
\r (Mat. 13:53-58; Luke 4:16-30)
\p
\v 1 SoВҰ26113 Yeshua leftВҰ26114 Capernaum andВҰ26113 wentВҰ26114 back with his followersВҰ26124 to \add Nazareth,\add* his birthplace.
\v 2 It was now the Rest Day and when he started teachingВҰ26136 in the meetingВҰ26139 hallВҰ26139, many who heard him were astonishedВҰ26146, sayingВҰ26151, вҖңWhere did he learn all this? How could he have such wisdomВҰ26160 and be able to do theseВҰ26154 miraclesВҰ26169?
\v 3 Isn't this the carpenterВҰ26183, the son of MariaВҰ26188, and the brotherВҰ26191 of Yacob and Yosef and YudasВҰ26198 and SimonВҰ26200? Don'tВҰ26178 his sistersВҰ26207 live around here?вҖқ And theyВҰ26214 were offendedВҰ26214 by his teaching.
\p
\v 4 \x + \xo 6:4: \xt Yhn 4:44.\x*\nd Yeshua\nd* told them, вҖң\wj A prophetВҰ26226 is only dishonouredВҰ26227 in his own home town, and amongВҰ26237 his own relativesВҰ26240, and in his own home.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 5 And he wasn't able to doВҰ26251 even one miracleВҰ26255 thereВҰ26250, exceptВҰ26257 for placing his handsВҰ26263 on a few sickВҰ26260 people andВҰ26247 healing them.
\v 6 He was amazed at how they wouldn't believe him as he went around the villagesВҰ26278 teachingВҰ26281.
\s1 Yeshua sends his apprentices out in pairs
\rem /s1 Jesus Sends Out the Twelve Disciples; Jesus Sends Out the Twelve Apostles; Death of John the Baptist; The Mission of the Twelve
\r (Mat. 10:5-15; Luke 9:1-6)
\p
\v 7 ThenВҰ26282 he called his twelveВҰ26286 apprentices and started sendingВҰ26291 them out in pairs and givingВҰ26298 them authorityВҰ26302 over demonsВҰ26306.
\v 8 He insisted that theyВҰ26313 can carry a walking stick butВҰ26307 not to take foodВҰ26322, a backpack, or moneyВҰ26335.
\v 9 They could wear one pair of sandalsВҰ26338, butВҰ26336 not take changes of clothes.
\v 10 And heВҰ26347 told them, вҖң\wj Whenever you are invited into a home, stay at that one place untilВҰ26360 you leave that town.\wj*
\v 11 \x + \xo 6:11: \xt Acts 13:51.\x*\wj ButВҰ26364 if any places don't want you or don't want to hearВҰ26375 what you have to say, just leave that placeВҰ26369. As you go, shakeВҰ26380 the dust off yourВҰ26387 sandals so they can see \+add that you pass the responsibility of what happened to them\+add*.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 12 SoВҰ26407 the apprentices went off andВҰ26407 started tellingВҰ26410 people to repentВҰ26413.
\v 13 \x + \xo 6:13: \xt Jam 5:14.\x*And they drove out many demonsВҰ26416, and anointedВҰ26422 many sickВҰ26427 people with oliveВҰ26424 oilВҰ26424 and healedВҰ26429 them.
\s1 The execution of Yohan-the-immerser
\rem /s1 The Death of John the Baptist; John the Baptist Beheaded
\r (Mat. 14:1-12; Luke 9:7-9)
\p
\v 14 \x + \xo 6:14-15: \xt Mat 16:14; Mrk 8:28; Luk 9:19.\x*Yeshua was now becoming well known and KingВҰ26435 HerodВҰ26436 \add Antipas\add* heardВҰ26432 about him. He thought that maybe Yohan-the-immerser had come back to life and that's why he was able to do miraclesВҰ26462.
\p
\v 15 ButВҰ26473 others thought it was \add the promised return of\add* Eliyah, andВҰ26473 yet others thought he must be another prophetВҰ26476 like the ones \add in the Scriptures\add*.
\p
\v 16 But hearing about Yeshua, HerodВҰ26486 was telling people, вҖңThat Yohan who I had beheadedВҰ26493, he must have come back to life!вҖқ
\v 17 \x + \xo 6:17-18: \xt Luk 3:19-20.\x*BecauseВҰ26508 HerodВҰ26510 himselfВҰ26506 had had Yohan arrested and put in prisonВҰ26525 becauseВҰ26508 he had marriedВҰ26538 HerodiasВҰ26528, hisВҰ26534 brotherВҰ26533 Philip's wifeВҰ26530.
\v 18 Yohan had been telling him that it was wrong for him to marry his brother'sВҰ26557 wifeВҰ26554,
\v 19 andВҰ26560 so HerodiasВҰ26561 resentedВҰ26563 him enough to want to killВҰ26570 him, butВҰ26560 Herod hadn't be able to
\v 20 becauseВҰ26576 he respected Yohan as a righteousВҰ26584 and holy teacher and so he kept him alive. He often enjoyed hearingВҰ26601 from Yohan and thought a lot about what he said.
\p
\v 21 However, an opportunityВҰ26606 came at Herod's birthdayВҰ26611 celebrationВҰ26611, when he threw a feast for hisВҰ26612 top officials and generals and for the leadersВҰ26624 in GalileeВҰ26626.
\v 22 The daughterВҰ26632 of HerodiasВҰ26636 came in and dancedВҰ26638 for them, and the king and his party guests all enjoyed it. SoВҰ26627 the king said to the young woman, вҖңJust ask me for anything and I'llВҰ26666 give it to you.вҖқ
\v 23 And he made an oath, вҖңEven if you asked for half of myВҰ26690 kingdomВҰ26689, I'd give it to you!вҖқ
\p
\v 24 SoВҰ26693 she went out andВҰ26693 asked her mother what she should ask for. HerВҰ26698 mother told her that she should ask for Yohan's headВҰ26707.
\p
\v 25 SoВҰ26713 going back into the party, sheВҰ26722 saidВҰ26723 seriously to the kingВҰ26721, вҖңI would like the headВҰ26739 of Yohan-the-immerser on a plate!вҖқ
\p
\v 26 The kingВҰ26747 was really upset with that, butВҰ26743 becauseВҰ26750 he had made loud oathsВҰ26752 in front of all his guests, he couldn't say no.
\v 27 SoВҰ26763 he orderedВҰ26770 an executionerВҰ26769 to go out and return with Yohan's headВҰ26775. He went off and beheadedВҰ26783 him in the prisonВҰ26787
\v 28 and broughtВҰ26789 the head into the party on a plate and gave it to the girl, and she gave it to herВҰ26808 motherВҰ26807.
\v 29 WhenВҰ26809 Yohan's followers heardВҰ26810 about this, they cameВҰ26815 and fetched hisВҰ26814 body and put it into a tombВҰ26828.
\s1 Yeshua feeds 5,000 people
\rem /s1 Miracles of feeding and their significance; Jesus Feeds Five Thousand; Feeding the Five Thousand
\r (Yhn 6:1-14; Mat. 14:13-21; Luke 9:10-17)
\p
\v 30 Now the apprentices who had been sent out returned back to \nd Yeshua\nd* and they reportedВҰ26837 back everything they had done and what they had been teaching \add people\add*.
\v 31 ThenВҰ26848 he told them, вҖң\wj Let's just all of us head for a quietВҰ26861 placeВҰ26862 and take a break.\wj*вҖқ This was becauseВҰ26870 there were so many people always comingВҰ26872 and goingВҰ26875, and sometimes they didn'tВҰ26878 even have a chance to eatВҰ26879.
\v 32 SoВҰ26883 theyВҰ26885 wentВҰ26885 by boatВҰ26890 away to a quietВҰ26894 placeВҰ26895 by themselvesВҰ26899.
\p
\v 33 ButВҰ26900 people from towns all around had seen them goingВҰ26904 and recognisedВҰ26910 who they were, so they ranВҰ26922 around the lake on footВҰ26915 and got thereВҰ26923 aheadВҰ26925 of them.
\v 34 \x + \xo 6:34: \xt Num 27:17; 1Ki 22:17; 2Ch 18:16; Eze 34:5; Mat 9:36.\x*SoВҰ26933 when Yeshua got out of the boat, he sawВҰ26938 a big crowdВҰ26943 andВҰ26933 felt sorry for them becauseВҰ26952 they seemed like sheepВҰ26955 without a shepherdВҰ26958, so he started teachingВҰ26962 them many things.
\v 35 ThenВҰ26966, when it was already getting late, hisВҰ26977 apprenticesВҰ26976 came up and saidВҰ26980, вҖңThis placeВҰ26986 is pretty isolated and it's already late.
\v 36 Send these people off now so they can go to the nearby settlements and villagesВҰ27004 and buy themselvesВҰ27007 somethingВҰ27010 to eatВҰ27012.вҖқ
\p
\v 37 ButВҰ27029 Yeshua answeredВҰ27019 them, вҖң\wj You give them something to eat.\wj*вҖқ
\p They complained, вҖңIf we go, should we buy several months wages worth of bread so we can give all of them something to eat?вҖқ
\p
\v 38 ButВҰ27052 heВҰ27050 asked, вҖң\wj Go and find out how much bread youВҰ27059 have.\wj*вҖқ
\p WhenВҰ27052 they'd found out they saidВҰ27053, вҖңFive buns and twoВҰ27072 fish.вҖқ
\p
\v 39 Yeshua toldВҰ27075 all the people to line up in rows andВҰ27074 sitВҰ27079 down on the greenВҰ27090 grassВҰ27091.
\v 40 SoВҰ27092 they satВҰ27093 down in rows of fiftyВҰ27103 to a hundredВҰ27099.
\v 41 ThenВҰ27104 holding the five buns and two fish, he looking up to the skyВҰ27116 and blessedВҰ27117 \add God\add*, and thenВҰ27104 brokeВҰ27120 up the buns and gave pieces to hisВҰ27128 apprenticesВҰ27127 so they could do likewise to the people, and he also dividedВҰ27139 up the two fish,
\v 42 and all the people ateВҰ27142 and were satisfiedВҰ27145.
\v 43 ThenВҰ27146 theyВҰ27147 collected the leftover pieces of bread, fillingВҰ27153 twelveВҰ27150 basketsВҰ27152, as well as the leftover pieces of fish.
\v 44 And the headcount of menВҰ27170 who ate that evening was fiveВҰ27168 thousandВҰ27168.
\s1 Yeshua walks on the lake surface
\rem /s1 Jesus Walks on the Water
\r (Yhn 6:15-21; Mat. 14:22-33)
\p
\v 45 Straight after that, Yeshua sent hisВҰ27177 apprenticesВҰ27176 off in the boatВҰ27181 to go acrossВҰ27188 to BethsaidaВҰ27190 while he sent the crowdВҰ27198 home.
\v 46 ThenВҰ27199 he said goodbyeВҰ27200 to everyone, andВҰ27199 climbed the hillВҰ27205 to pray.
\v 47 Later in the night, the boatВҰ27213 was out in the middle of the lakeВҰ27219, andВҰ27207 only Yeshua remained back there on the land.
\v 48 He saw them struggling to row against the windВҰ27242, andВҰ27228 sometime after 3am he came out to them, walkingВҰ27257 on the lakeВҰ27262 surface as if to walkВҰ27257 past them.
\v 49 ButВҰ27270 they had seenВҰ27271 someone walkingВҰ27277 on the lakeВҰ27276 and thought it was a ghostВҰ27280, and they yelledВҰ27285 out
\v 50 becauseВҰ27287 they had all seen it and were terrified.
\p ButВҰ27294 Yeshua immediatelyВҰ27295 spokeВҰ27296 to them and saidВҰ27302, вҖң\wj Hey, take heart, it's me, don'tВҰ27308 be afraid!\wj*вҖқ
\v 51 ThenВҰ27312 he climbed up into the boatВҰ27318 andВҰ27312 the windВҰ27324 diedВҰ27322 down. And they were all totally astounded
\v 52 because theyВҰ27337 hadn't understoodВҰ27337 the implications of him feeding all the people because theirВҰ27344 minds were closed.
\s1 Yeshua heals many people around Gennesaret
\rem /s1 Healing the Sick in Gennesaret; Jesus Heals the Sick in Gennesaret
\r (Mat. 14:34-36)
\p
\v 53 After completing their crossingВҰ27350, theyВҰ27356 anchoredВҰ27360 at GennesaretВҰ27358.
\v 54 And when they got out of the boatВҰ27366, again people recognisedВҰ27368 Yeshua
\v 55 and ranВҰ27377 aroundВҰ27377 that region, so next minute people beganВҰ27386 bringing all of those who were sickВҰ27395, carryingВҰ27397 them on palletsВҰ27391 to whereverВҰ27401 they heard that Yeshua was.
\v 56 And whenever Yeshua enteredВҰ27420 villagesВҰ27423 or citiesВҰ27426 or fieldsВҰ27429 or marketplacesВҰ27438, they laid the sick down there and were imploringВҰ27443 him that they might even just touchВҰ27452 the edge of hisВҰ27451 robe, and anyone who did so was healedВҰ27460.
\c 7
\s1 Yeshua suggests obeying God, not tradition
\rem /s1 The Tradition of the Elders; The Teaching of the Ancestors; Clean and Unclean; Jesus Teaches about Inner Purity
\r (Mat. 15:1-9)
\p
\v 1 Some from the Pharisee partyВҰ27466 andВҰ27467 some of the law teachersВҰ27470 had comeВҰ27471 from Yerushalem to observe Yeshua
\v 2 andВҰ27474 noticed that some of hisВҰ27481 followers were eatingВҰ27490 their food without following their religious customs, i.e., without washing their handsВҰ27485.
\v 3 (The Pharisees andВҰ27499, in fact, all the Jewish religious leaders do not eat without first ceremonially washing their handsВҰ27509 as taught by their eldersВҰ27519 over the generations.
\v 4 They won'tВҰ27530 eat at the marketВҰ27522 if they can'tВҰ27530 do this first, and have many otherВҰ27533 regulations about ceremonial washingВҰ27543 of cups and jugs and copperВҰ27548 kettlesВҰ27548.)
\p
\v 5 And the Pharisees andВҰ27558 religiousВҰ27560 teachersВҰ27560 asked Yeshua, вҖңHow come yourВҰ27568 followers don'tВҰ27569 follow our Jewish traditionsВҰ27573, butВҰ27576 eat without the ceremonial washing of handsВҰ27582?вҖқ
\p
\v 6 And he answeredВҰ27588, вҖң\wj Yeshayah got it exactly rightВҰ27592 when he expressed God's thoughts about you hypocritesВҰ27599 andВҰ27587 wroteВҰ27602:\wj*\x + \xo 7:6-7: \xt Isa 29:13 (LXX).\x*
\q1 \wj вҖҳThese peopleВҰ27607 honourВҰ27613 me with their lipsВҰ27610,\wj*
\q2 \wj butВҰ27587 their real desires are far away from mine.\wj*
\q1
\v 7 \wj Their worshipВҰ27626 of me is worthless,\wj*
\q2 \wj teachingВҰ27628 man-made rules as if theyВҰ27626 are from God.вҖҷ\wj*
\p
\v 8 \wj You've ignored God's commandsВҰ27647 instead accepting humanВҰ27655 traditionsВҰ27653.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 9 And Yeshua continued, вҖң\wj You all simply dismiss God's commandsВҰ27673 in favour of yourВҰ27679 own customs.\wj*
\v 10 \x + \xo 7:10: a \xt Exo 20:12; Deu 5:16; \xo b \xt Exo 21:17; Lev 20:9.\x*\wj Mosheh teaches us,\wj*
\q1 \wj вҖҳHonour yourВҰ27689 parents,вҖҷ\wj*
\p \wj and\wj*
\q1 \wj вҖҳAnyone dishonestly slandering their parents deserves the deathВҰ27701 penalty.вҖҷ\wj*
\m
\v 11 \wj But when you all encourage people to sayВҰ27709, вҖҳWhatever I had that may have helped you guys has been given to GodвҖҷ,\wj*
\v 12 \wj youВҰ27730 are actively discouraging them from helping their parentsвҖ”\wj*
\v 13 \wj overriding God's voice for yourВҰ27751 very convenient teaching that you disseminate instead. And that's not the only example!\wj*вҖқ
\s1 Evil comes from inside a person
\rem /s1 The Things That Make a Person Unclean
\r (Mat. 15:10-20)
\p
\v 14 Yeshua calledВҰ27765 out to the crowdВҰ27769, вҖң\wj Everyone listen to me carefully:\wj*
\v 15 \wj Nothing that entersВҰ27787 your mouth makes you guilty in God's eyes. It's what comes \+em out\+em* of you that demonstrates your culpability.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 16 в—ҳ
\v 17 WhenВҰ27819 Yeshua cameВҰ27821 back inside, hisВҰ27835 apprenticesВҰ27834 asked him what he meant.
\v 18 ButВҰ27841 he scolded them, вҖң\wj Can't you understandВҰ27851 something so simple! Can't you see that anything from the outsideВҰ27856 that entersВҰ27857 your body doesn't make you guilty in God's sight,\wj*
\v 19 \wj becauseВҰ27867 it doesn't enterВҰ27871 your mindВҰ27876 butВҰ27882 merely goes into your stomach and ends up in the toilet.\wj*вҖқ (By saying this he clearly showed that is was ok for Jews to eat any food.)
\p
\v 20 He continued, вҖң\wj It's what comes out of you that makes you guilty in God's eyes.\wj*
\v 21-22 \wj That's becauseВҰ27912 evilВҰ27921 thoughts, sexualВҰ27924 immoralityВҰ27924, theftВҰ27926, murderВҰ27929, adulteryВҰ27931, greed, wickedness, deceit, arrogance, lust, slander, pride, and foolishness all come from \+em insideВҰ27911\+em* people'sВҰ27917 heartsВҰ27915 \+add and minds\+add*.\wj*
\v 23 \wj So it's the evilВҰ27950 that's insideВҰ27951 a personВҰ27958 andВҰ27954 comes out that makes them guilty in God's eyes.\wj*вҖқ
\s1 The bold faith of a non-Jewish woman
\rem /s1 The Faith of a Syrophoenician Woman; A Woman's Faith; The Faith of a Gentile Woman; The Syrophoenician Woman's Faith
\r (Mat. 15:21-28)
\p
\v 24 Yeshua left that place and wentВҰ27964 \add up north\add* into the regionsВҰ27967 of TyreВҰ27969 and Tsidon. He tried to enter a houseВҰ27976 without being noticedВҰ27985 butВҰ27961 didn'tВҰ27982 succeed,
\v 25 and straight away a womanВҰ27993 who had heardВҰ27991 aboutВҰ27994 him turned up. She knelt in front of him because she had a littleВҰ27999 daughterВҰ27999 who was demon-possessed.
\v 26 The womanВҰ28019 was GreekВҰ28021 from PhoeniciaВҰ28023 in SyriaВҰ28023 andВҰ28026 sheВҰ28027 begged Yeshua to command the demonВҰ28031 to leave herВҰ28038 daughterВҰ28037.
\v 27 ButВҰ28040 he replied, вҖң\wj Let the \+add Jewish\+add* children be treated firstВҰ28048, becauseВҰ28053 it's not good to take the children's foodВҰ28059 andВҰ28040 throwВҰ28066 it to the dogs.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 28 And she responded, вҖңYes, \nd masterВҰ28075\nd*, butВҰ28068 the puppies under the tableВҰ28086 \em do\em* get to eat the little crumbsВҰ28092 that the childrenВҰ28096 drop.вҖқ
\p
\v 29 And he answered, вҖң\wj Go home now. As a result of how you just spoke, the demonВҰ28108 has already left yourВҰ28112 daughterВҰ28111.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 30 And when sheВҰ28122 got homeВҰ28119, the demonВҰ28140 had indeed gone andВҰ28115 her littleВҰ28129 girl was lying quietly on her bed.
\s1 Yeshua heals a deaf man who couldn't speak
\rem /s1 Jesus Heals a Deaf-Mute; Jesus Cures a Deaf Man; The Healing of a Deaf and Mute Man; Jesus Heals a Deaf and Mute Man
\p
\v 31 Yeshua left the TyreВҰ28148 region, passed throughВҰ28150 Tsidon, andВҰ28142 cameВҰ28149 down the \add eastern\add* side of the Lake of GalileeВҰ28159 to the DecapolisВҰ28167 region.
\v 32 The people there brought a manВҰ28174 to him who couldn't hear or speak, andВҰ28169 asked Yeshua to heal him.
\v 33 SoВҰ28185 Yeshua took the man back away from the crowdВҰ28193, put hisВҰ28202 fingersВҰ28201 in the man's earsВҰ28206, thenВҰ28185 he spat andВҰ28185 touchedВҰ28211 the man's mouth.
\v 34 Looking up to the skyВҰ28220, he sighed and saidВҰ28224, вҖң\wj Open up!\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 35 ThenВҰ28230 the man could hear, and hisВҰ28234 tongueВҰ28246 was released and he began to speakВҰ28249 properly.
\v 36 The Yeshua advised that they shouldn't tell anyoneВҰ28255, butВҰ28262 the more heВҰ28252 said that, the more they seemed to spread itВҰ28269 around.
\v 37 The crowds were totally amazedВҰ28273, sayingВҰ28274, вҖңHe can do anythingвҖ”he makes the deaf able to hearВҰ28284, andВҰ28270 enables the ones who couldn't speakВҰ28288.вҖқ
\c 8
\s1 Yeshua feeds 4,000 people
\rem /s1 Jesus Feeds Four Thousand People; Feeding the Four Thousand; Jesus Feeds the Four Thousand
\r (Mat. 15:32-39)
\p
\v 1 Another timeВҰ28293 there was a largeВҰ28296 crowdВҰ28297 againВҰ28295 with nothing to eat. Yeshua calledВҰ28305 hisВҰ28310 apprenticesВҰ28309 and told them,
\v 2 вҖң\wj I feel sorry for all these people becauseВҰ28322 they've alreadyВҰ28323 been with us for threeВҰ28327 daysВҰ28324 andВҰ28336 don'tВҰ28337 have anythingВҰ28339 to eatВҰ28340.\wj*
\v 3 \wj I can't send them homeВҰ28349 because they're too weak to walk, andВҰ28341 some have a long way to go.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 4 HisВҰ28375 apprenticesВҰ28374 queried, вҖңWhere could anyoneВҰ28386 find enough food out here in the wildernessВҰ28392?вҖқ
\p
\v 5 He asked, вҖң\wj How much bread have youВҰ28404 all got?\wj*вҖқ
\p вҖңSevenВҰ28410 buns,вҖқ theyВҰ28407 answered.
\p
\v 6 SoВҰ28411 Yeshua instructed the crowd to sit down on the groundВҰ28419. ThenВҰ28411 he took the sevenВҰ28423 buns, gave thanksВҰ28426 and brokeВҰ28427 them and gave pieces to hisВҰ28433 apprenticesВҰ28432 to thenВҰ28411 distribute to the crowd.
\v 7 They also had a few smallВҰ28442 cooked fish, so heВҰ28450 blessedВҰ28447 them too andВҰ28444 got them to distribute them as well.
\v 8 After all the people had eaten andВҰ28463 were full, they collected sevenВҰ28477 basketfulsВҰ28478 of leftovers.
\v 9 There were some fourВҰ28486 thousandВҰ28486 people there that day, andВҰ28482 Yeshua sentВҰ28488 them home after they'd eatenВҰ28484.
\v 10 And he and hisВҰ28502 apprenticesВҰ28501 climbed into the boatВҰ28498 and headed for the DalmanuthaВҰ28514 region.
\s1 The religious leaders want to see a miracle
\rem /s1 The Demand for a Sign; Pharisees Demand a Miraculous Sign; The Pharisees Ask for a Miracle
\r (Mat. 16:1-4)
\p
\v 11 \x + \xo 8:11: \xt Mat 12:38; Luk 11:16.\x*Some men from the Pharisee partyВҰ28519 cameВҰ28517 out to Yeshua and started arguing with him. They were checking him out and wanted to see a miracle.
\v 12 \x + \xo 8:12: \xt Mat 12:39; Luk 11:29.\x*Yeshua grieved inside andВҰ28541 asked, вҖң\wj Why do you people need to see a miracle before you'll believe me? Actually, no miracle will be done for this generation.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 13 SoВҰ28568 Yeshua left in the boat againВҰ28573 andВҰ28568 crossed to the otherВҰ28581 sideВҰ28580 of the lake.
\s1 The apprentices miss the significance of what's happening
\rem /s1 The Yeast of the Pharisees and of Herod; Yeast of the Pharisees and Herod
\r (Mat. 16:5-12)
\p
\v 14 ButВҰ28582 Yeshua's apprentices forgotВҰ28584 to takeВҰ28588 any food other than one bun that someone in the boatВҰ28604 had.
\v 15 \x + \xo 8:15: \xt Luk 12:1.\x*He told them, вҖң\wj Watch out for the yeast of the Pharisees andВҰ28618 of King HerodВҰ28624.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 16 They asked each other what it meantвҖ”was it becauseВҰ28632 they forgot food?
\p
\v 17 ButВҰ28638 \nd Yeshua\nd* knew what they were sayingВҰ28642 andВҰ28638 asked, вҖң\wj Why are you all discussing about not having food? Can't you figure itВҰ28639 out? Or are yourВҰ28670 minds completely closed?\wj*
\v 18 \x + \xo 8:18: \xt Jer 5:21; Eze 12:2; Mrk 4:12.\x*\wj You all have eyesВҰ28671 but can't seem to see andВҰ28679 have earsВҰ28680 but can't seem to listen. Have you already forgotten what just happened?\wj*
\v 19 \wj When I brokeВҰ28700 up the five buns to feed five thousandВҰ28703 people, how many basketfulsВҰ28706 of leftovers did you collect?\wj*вҖқ
\p вҖңTwelveВҰ28714,вҖқ they answered.
\p
\v 20 вҖңAnd when we fed fourВҰ28723 thousandВҰ28723 with sevenВҰ28719 buns, how many full basketsВҰ28726 of leftovers thenВҰ28716?вҖқ
\p вҖңSevenВҰ28739,вҖқ theyВҰ28737 answered.
\p
\v 21 Yeshua asked, вҖң\wj How can you all not understandВҰ28749 what's going on right in front of you!\wj*вҖқ
\s1 Yeshua heals a blind man near Bethsaida
\rem /s1 The Healing of a Blind Man at Bethsaida; Jesus Heals a Blind Man at Bethsaida; Jesus Cures a Blind Man at Bethsaida
\p
\v 22 As they entered BethsaidaВҰ28755, the people brought a blindВҰ28759 manВҰ28759 to Yeshua andВҰ28750 asked him to touchВҰ28765 him.
\v 23 SoВҰ28766 Yeshua took the man's handВҰ28771 and led him out of the villageВҰ28781. ThenВҰ28766 he spat in his eyesВҰ28787, placedВҰ28790 his handsВҰ28792 on him, and asked him, вҖң\wj What can you see?\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 24 The man lookedВҰ28807 around andВҰ28805 answered, вҖңI can see the peopleВҰ28814, butВҰ28805 they just look like treesВҰ28818.вҖқ
\v 25 Yeshua touched the man's eyesВҰ28832 againВҰ28823 and then he could see clearlyвҖ”he was now completely better.
\v 26 ThenВҰ28856 Yeshua told him not to go back into the villageВҰ28880 butВҰ28856 to go straight homeВҰ28861.
\s1 Yeshua asks who they think he is
\rem /s1 The cross foreshadowed; Peter's Confession of Christ; Peter's Declaration about Jesus
\r (Mat. 16:13-20; Luke 9:18-21)
\p
\v 27 ThenВҰ28889 \nd Yeshua\nd* andВҰ28889 hisВҰ28896 followers moved around the various villagesВҰ28899 of Caesaria PhilippiВҰ28903. On the way, he asked them, вҖң\wj Who does everyoneВҰ28921 think I am?\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 28 \x + \xo 8:28: \xt Mrk 6:14-15; Luk 9:7-8.\x*They saidВҰ28928, вҖңSome say Yohan-the-immerser, some say Eliyah, andВҰ28935 some say one of the prophetsВҰ28946.вҖқ
\p
\v 29 \x + \xo 8:29: \xt Yhn 6:68-69.\x*ThenВҰ28947 he asked, вҖң\wj And what do you all think?\wj*вҖқ
\p PeterВҰ28964 saidВҰ28958, вҖңYou are the promised one sent by God.вҖқ
\p
\v 30 ThenВҰ28977 Yeshua warnedВҰ28978 them not to tell others about himВҰ28987.
\s1 Yeshua's radical challenge to his would-be followers
\rem /s1 Jesus Foretells His Death and Resurrection; Jesus Speaks about His Suffering and Death; Jesus Predicts His Death
\r (Mat. 16:21-28; Luke 9:22-27)
\p
\v 31 ThenВҰ28988 Yeshua beganВҰ28991 teachingВҰ28992 his followers that humanity's child would need to sufferВҰ29001 a lot, to be rejectedВҰ29003 by the religious leaders, andВҰ28988 so to be put to death butВҰ28988 to come back to life afterВҰ29018 threeВҰ29020 daysВҰ29022.
\v 32 He taught this very clearly, butВҰ29025 PeterВҰ29034 took him asideВҰ29031 andВҰ29025 told him off.
\v 33 Yeshua turnedВҰ29042 back andВҰ29040 looked at the others, thenВҰ29040 reprimanded PeterВҰ29051, вҖң\wj Stand back, SatanВҰ29058! you'reВҰ29061 applying humanВҰ29068 values instead of considering God's plan.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 34 \x + \xo 8:34: \xt Mat 10:38; Luk 14:27.\x*Calling out to them and to the crowdВҰ29072, he saidВҰ29077, вҖң\wj Anyone who wants to follow me must first put aside their own desires and thenВҰ29069 follow meвҖ”even through very difficult times.\wj*
\v 35 \x + \xo 8:35: \xt Yhn 12:25; Mat 10:39; Luk 17:33.\x*\wj Anyone who worries about savingВҰ29128 their own life will lose it, butВҰ29124 anyone who gives their life due to following me and my teaching will save their life.\wj*
\v 36 \wj BecauseВҰ29131 itВҰ29133 doesn't benefitВҰ29133 a personВҰ29135 if they gain everything in the worldВҰ29141 butВҰ29144 lose their soulВҰ29149.\wj*
\v 37 \wj What can someone offer in order to buy a home for their soulВҰ29160?\wj*
\v 38 \wj Yes, anyone who is ashamed of me and myВҰ29169 messageВҰ29176 in front of this adulterousВҰ29182 and sinfulВҰ29184 generationВҰ29179, humanity's child will likewise be ashamed of them when he comes clearly displaying God's greatness and bringing the holy messengersВҰ29203.\wj*вҖқ
\c 9
\p
\v 1 And he continued, вҖңI can assure you that some of the ones standing here won'tВҰ29224 die untilВҰ29227 they have seen God's powerfulВҰ29236 kingdomВҰ29231 arrive.вҖқ
\s1 Mosheh and Eliyah speak with Yeshua
\rem /s1 The Transfiguration
\r (Mat. 17:1-13; Luke 9:28-36)
\p
\v 2 \x + \xo 9:2-7: \xt 2Pe 1:17-18.\x*Six daysВҰ29239 later \nd Yeshua\nd* took PeterВҰ29246 and Yacob and Yohan, and just the four of them went up onto a highВҰ29260 hillВҰ29259. ThenВҰ29237 he was changed right in front of their eyes
\v 3 andВҰ29278 hisВҰ29281 clothesВҰ29280 turned incredibly shiningВҰ29284 whiteвҖ”whiter than any bleach could make them.
\v 4 And Eliyah and Mosheh appearedВҰ29306 beside \nd Yeshua\nd* and started talking with him.
\v 5 PeterВҰ29322 saidВҰ29323 to \nd Yeshua\nd*, вҖңTeacher, it's goodВҰ29329 that we're here. Maybe we could make threeВҰ29341 shelters up here: one for youВҰ29343 and one for Mosheh and one for Eliyah?вҖқ
\v 6 He said that becauseВҰ29362 theyВҰ29363 were terrifiedВҰ29361 and didn'tВҰ29351 know what to say.
\p
\v 7 \x + \xo 9:7: \xt Mat 3:17; Mrk 1:11; Luk 3:22.\x*ThenВҰ29365 a cloud came over the sun andВҰ29365 a voiceВҰ29375 came out of the cloud saying, вҖңThis is myВҰ29386 dear son. Listen to him.вҖқ
\v 8 WhenВҰ29395 they lookedВҰ29398 aroundВҰ29398, they couldn't see anyoneВҰ29401 else there any more, exceptВҰ29405 for \nd YeshuaВҰ29409\nd* himself.
\rem /s1 The Coming of Elijah
\p
\v 9 As they descended again, Yeshua told them to tell no one what had happened up there until after humanity's child came back to life.
\p
\v 10 They remembered that, although between all three of them theyВҰ29445 couldn't understand the bit about coming back to life.
\v 11 \x + \xo 9:11: \xt Mal 4:5; Mat 11:14.\x*They asked Yeshua, вҖңIsn't itВҰ29474 written that Eliyah will be the firstВҰ29477 to return?вҖқ
\p
\v 12 He answered, вҖңYes, Eliyah is indeedВҰ29487 the one to comeВҰ29488 firstВҰ29490 to start the restorationВҰ29491. ButВҰ29480 isn't itВҰ29498 also writtenВҰ29498 that humanity's child will sufferВҰ29506 a lot andВҰ29507 be scornedВҰ29508?
\v 13 You see, Eliyah has comeВҰ29517 already, and they treated him just however they liked, just like it was writtenВҰ29526 that it would happen.вҖқ
\s1 Yeshua drives out a stubborn demon
\rem /s1 Jesus Heals a Boy with an Evil Spirit; The Healing of a Boy with a Spirit; The Healing of a Boy with an Evil Spirit; Jesus Heals a Boy Possessed by an Evil Spirit
\r (Mat. 17:14-21; Luke 9:37-43a)
\p
\v 14 WhenВҰ29530 they got back to \add his other\add* followers, Yeshua sawВҰ29536 that they were surrounded by a largeВҰ29539 crowdВҰ29538 andВҰ29543 the religiousВҰ29545 teachersВҰ29545 were debatingВҰ29546 with them.
\v 15 The crowdВҰ29555 were very surprised when they noticed Yeshua andВҰ29551 came runningВҰ29567 to greetВҰ29568 him.
\v 16 He askedВҰ29571 them, вҖң\wj What were youВҰ29576 all talking about?\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 17 One of the people answeredВҰ29584, вҖңTeacherВҰ29593, I broughtВҰ29594 myВҰ29597 son hereвҖ”he has a demon that prevents him from speaking.
\v 18 Whenever it takes hold of him, it attacksВҰ29610 him and he starts foamingВҰ29613 at the mouth and gratingВҰ29615 his teethВҰ29617 and his joints lock up. I tried to get yourВҰ29625 followers to command it to leave butВҰ29603 they couldn't.вҖқ
\p
\v 19 Yeshua replied, вҖң\wj You are a faithless generationВҰ29646. How much longer will I have to be here? How much longer can I tolerateВҰ29657 you all? Bring himВҰ29661 here.\wj*вҖқ
\v 20 SoВҰ29664 they broughtВҰ29665 the boy to him. WhenВҰ29664 he saw Yeshua, the demon immediatelyВҰ29675 caused him to have convulsionsВҰ29676 and fall on the groundВҰ29684вҖ”rollingВҰ29685 over and foamingВҰ29686 at the mouth.
\p
\v 21 Yeshua askedВҰ29688 hisВҰ29692 fatherВҰ29691, вҖң\wj How long has this been happening?\wj*вҖқ
\p вҖңSince he was small,вҖқ he replied,
\v 22 вҖңand oftenВҰ29711 it throwsВҰ29718 him into the fireВҰ29716 or into waterВҰ29721 to try to destroyВҰ29724 him. ButВҰ29710 if you feel sorry for us and can do it, please helpВҰ29733 us.вҖқ
\p
\v 23 \nd Yeshua\nd* asked himВҰ29744, вҖң\wj If I can? A person who believesВҰ29754 can do anything.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 24 The boys fatherВҰ29760 criedВҰ29757 out, вҖңI do believeВҰ29770вҖ”helpВҰ29772 me to fight unbeliefВҰ29776.вҖқ
\p
\v 25 ThenВҰ29782 \nd Yeshua\nd* noticing that a big crowdВҰ29789 was quickly forming, scolded the evil spirit, вҖң\wj You spirit who causes muteness and deafness. Leave this boy now and never return to him.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 26 There was yelling and strong convulsionsВҰ29825, and thenВҰ29819 the demon leftВҰ29827 him and the boy lay still as if deadВҰ29834, and many people thought he was.
\v 27 ButВҰ29843 \nd YeshuaВҰ29844\nd* took hisВҰ29849 handВҰ29848 and lifted it, and the boy got up.
\p
\v 28 WhenВҰ29854 Yeshua andВҰ29854 hisВҰ29868 apprenticesВҰ29867 had gone into the houseВҰ29862 by themselvesВҰ29872, they asked him, вҖңHow comeВҰ29857 we couldn't drive itВҰ29889 out?вҖқ
\p
\v 29 He replied, вҖң\wj This kind will only leave after prayerВҰ29905 andВҰ29906 fastingВҰ29907.\wj*вҖқ
\s1 Yeshua talks again about being executed
\rem /s1 Learning what discipleship means; Jesus Again Predicts His Death; Jesus Again Foretells His Death and Resurrection; Jesus Speaks Again about His Death
\r (Mat. 17:22-23; Luke 9:43b-45)
\p
\v 30 ThenВҰ29908 they left that place andВҰ29908 were moving around GalileeВҰ29916, because Yeshua didn'tВҰ29918 want people to knowВҰ29922 where he was
\v 31 while he was teachingВҰ29923 hisВҰ29927 apprenticesВҰ29926. He told them, вҖң\wj Humanity's child will be arrested and executed, butВҰ29928 afterВҰ29947 threeВҰ29949 daysВҰ29951 he'll come back to life.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 32 ButВҰ29956 they didn'tВҰ29957 know what that meant, andВҰ29956 they were too scared to askВҰ29964 himВҰ29962.
\s1 How to be the best
\rem /s1 The Greatest in the Kingdom; Who Is the Greatest?
\r (Mat. 18:1-5; Luke 9:46-48)
\p
\v 33 ThenВҰ29965 they wentВҰ29966 to CapernaumВҰ29970 andВҰ29965 when they arrived at the houseВҰ29974, Yeshua asked them what they were discussing on the wayВҰ29981.
\p
\v 34 \x + \xo 9:34: \xt Luk 22:24.\x*ButВҰ29989 they didn't reply becauseВҰ29993 while they were walking, they had been talking about which of them is the best.
\v 35 \x + \xo 9:35: \xt Mat 20:26-27; 23:11; Mrk 10:43-44; Luk 22:26.\x*SoВҰ30007 Yeshua satВҰ30008 down and calledВҰ30009 the twelveВҰ30011 of them and explained, вҖң\wj Anyone who wants to be at the top, has to be at the bottom and help all the others.\wj*вҖқ
\v 36 ThenВҰ30026 Yeshua called a young boy and stoodВҰ30030 him in the middle of them, and giving him a hug saidВҰ30042,
\v 37 \x + \xo 9:37: \xt Yhn 13:20; Mat 10:40; Luk 10:16.\x*вҖң\wj WhoeverВҰ30044 welcomes young childrenВҰ30051 on myВҰ30059 behalf, welcomes me, andВҰ30062 anyoneВҰ30047 who welcomes me is not actually welcoming me, butВҰ30073 welcoming the one who sentВҰ30075 me here.\wj*вҖқ
\s1 Others are also serving Yeshua
\rem /s1 Whoever Is Not Against Us Is for Us; Another Exorcist; Using the Name of Jesus
\r (Luke 9:49-50)
\p
\v 38 Yohan checked with Yeshua, вҖңTeacherВҰ30088, we sawВҰ30089 someoneВҰ30090 using yourВҰ30094 authority to command demonsВҰ30096 to leave, butВҰ30104 we told him off becauseВҰ30108 he wasn't one of us.вҖқ
\p
\v 39 \nd Yeshua\nd* respondedВҰ30117, вҖң\wj No, don'tВҰ30118 stop himВҰ30120 becauseВҰ30122 anyoneВҰ30121 who does a miracleВҰ30126 using myВҰ30131 nameВҰ30130 won'tВҰ30118 just quicklyВҰ30135 turn around andВҰ30114 slander me.\wj*
\v 40 \x + \xo 9:40: \xt Mat 12:30; Luk 11:23.\x*\wj Anyone who's not againstВҰ30143 us is for us.\wj*
\v 41 \x + \xo 9:41: \xt Mat 10:42.\x*\wj \+nd AnyoneВҰ30165\+nd* who gives you waterВҰ30158 to drinkВҰ30155 because you are followers of God's \+nd chosenВҰ30165\+nd* one and who does it because they are working for me, I can assure you that they'll receive their rewardВҰ30177.\wj*
\s1 Difficult teachings about disobedience
\rem /s1 Causing to Sin; Temptations to Sin
\r (Mat. 18:6-9; Luke 17:1-2)
\p
\v 42 вҖң\wj ButВҰ30179 anyoneВҰ30185 who causes a young person to falter from their trust in me, itВҰ30197 would be betterВҰ30196 if they were thrownВҰ30216 into the seaВҰ30220 with a heavyВҰ30208 weight tied around their neck.\wj*
\v 43 \x + \xo 9:43: \xt Mat 5:30.\x*\wj If yourВҰ30229 handВҰ30228 causes you to disobey God, cut it offвҖ”it's betterВҰ30232 to enter \+add eternal\+add* lifeВҰ30241 being maimedВҰ30237, than to have twoВҰ30246 handsВҰ30247 butВҰ30222 to be thrown into the fireВҰ30259 that never goes out.\wj*
\v 44 в—ҳ
\v 45 \wj And if yourВҰ30278 footВҰ30277 causes you to disobey God, cut it offвҖ”it's betterВҰ30287 to enter \+add eternal\+add* lifeВҰ30297 being maimed, than to have twoВҰ30305 feetВҰ30306 butВҰ30274 to be thrownВҰ30309 into hell.\wj*
\v 46 в—ҳ
\v 47 \x + \xo 9:47: \xt Mat 5:29.\x*\wj And if yourВҰ30335 eyeВҰ30334 causes you to disobey God, gouge it outвҖ”it's betterВҰ30343 to enter God's kingdomВҰ30351 one-eyed, than to have twoВҰ30356 eyesВҰ30357 andВҰ30330 be thrownВҰ30341 into hell\wj*
\v 48 \wj whereВҰ30366 the worms never die andВҰ30372 the fireВҰ30374 never goes out.\wj*
\p
\v 49 вҖң\wj Everyone will be saltedВҰ30381 with fireВҰ30380.\wj*
\p
\v 50 \x + \xo 9:50: \xt Mat 5:13; Luk 14:34-35.\x*вҖң\wj Now salt is goodВҰ30389, butВҰ30393 if itВҰ30402 were to go bad, what would youВҰ30403 seasonВҰ30403 \+add your food\+add* with then? So keep yourselvesВҰ30408 like salt, andВҰ30411 strive to get on well with each other.\wj*вҖқ
\c 10
\s1 It's God that joins husband and wife
\rem /s1 Discussion about Divorce and Marriage; Teaching about Divorce; Jesus Teaches about Divorce
\r (Mat. 19:1-12; Luke 16:18)
\p
\v 1 ThenВҰ30416 Yeshua left \add Capernaum\add* and went down to the Yudean area and across the YordanВҰ30430 river. Again the crowdsВҰ30438 followed him, and he taughtВҰ30446 them just like he usually did.
\p
\v 2 Some from the Pharisee partyВҰ30452 approachedВҰ30449 Yeshua to check him out andВҰ30448 asked, вҖңDoes the law allow a husbandВҰ30465 to dismiss his wifeВҰ30466?вҖқ
\p
\v 3 вҖң\wj Well, what law did Mosheh give to youВҰ30476 all?\wj*вҖқ heВҰ30470 asked.
\p
\v 4 \x + \xo 10:4: \xt Deu 24:1-4; Mat 5:31.\x*They answered, вҖңMosheh saidВҰ30482 that a husband is allowed to writeВҰ30489 a statement of divorceВҰ30487 andВҰ30490 dismiss his wife with it.вҖқ
\p
\v 5 \nd Yeshua\nd* respondedВҰ30497, вҖң\wj Yes, he wroteВҰ30503 that law because he saw yourВҰ30502 stubborn desires,\wj*
\v 6 \x + \xo 10:6: \xt Gen 1:27; 5:2.\x*\wj butВҰ30510 God made both men andВҰ30514 women right at the beginningВҰ30511.\wj*
\v 7 \x + \xo 10:7-8: \xt Gen 2:24.\x*\wj As a result, a manВҰ30527 leaves his parents and joins together with his wifeВҰ30542\wj*
\v 8 \wj and the couple become a single unit. So there's no longerВҰ30554 two of them, butВҰ30545 only one.\wj*
\v 9 \wj SoВҰ30562 if it's \+nd GodВҰ30564\+nd* who joins them togetherВҰ30566 like that, no personВҰ30567 \+add has the authority\+add* to separateВҰ30569 them.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 10 Back in the houseВҰ30576 againВҰ30578, his apprenticesВҰ30581 asked about this.
\v 11 \x + \xo 10:11-12: \xt Mat 5:32; 1Cor 7:10-11.\x*And Yeshua told them, вҖң\wj WhoeverВҰ30598 divorces his wife andВҰ30595 marries anotherВҰ30612 person, commits adulteryВҰ30614 towards his wife.\wj*вҖқ
\v 12 \wj And likewise if the wife divorces her husband andВҰ30617 marries anotherВҰ30636 person, she is committing adulteryВҰ30639 towards her husband.\wj*вҖқ
\s1 Yeshua encourages childlike faith
\rem /s1 The Little Children and Jesus; Jesus Blesses Little Children; Jesus Blesses the Children
\r (Mat. 19:13-15; Luke 18:15-17)
\p
\v 13 The people were bringingВҰ30641 smallВҰ30643 childrenВҰ30643 for Yeshua to touchВҰ30647, butВҰ30649 his apprenticesВҰ30650 scolded them.
\v 14 However, \nd Yeshua\nd* noticed it and was upset, вҖң\wj Just let those kids come. Don'tВҰ30675 prevent them becauseВҰ30679 God's kingdomВҰ30683 consists of people like them.\wj*
\v 15 \x + \xo 10:15: \xt Mat 18:3.\x*\wj Actually, you can'tВҰ30694 even enter God's kingdomВҰ30697 unless you accept itВҰ30706 just like a smallВҰ30701 childВҰ30701 does.\wj*вҖқ
\v 16 SoВҰ30708 he continued hugging the children andВҰ30708 \add commanding\add* a good life for them as he placed his handsВҰ30717 on each one.
\s1 Leaving behind everything to be saved
\rem /s1 The Rich Man; The Rich Young Man
\r (Mat. 19:16-30; Luke 18:18-30)
\p
\v 17 One time when Yeshua was starting out on a trip, a man caught up to him andВҰ30723 kneeling down in front of him asked, вҖңGood teacher, what do I have to do to inheritВҰ30748 eternalВҰ30747 lifeВҰ30746?вҖқ
\p
\v 18 He answered, вҖң\wj Why do you call me \+em good\+em*? No person is goodвҖ”only \+nd GodВҰ30765\+nd* is.\wj*
\v 19 \x + \xo 10:19: a \xt Exo 20:13; Deu 5:17; \xo b \xt Exo 20:14; Deu 5:18; \xo c \xt Exo 20:15; Deu 5:19; \xo d \xt Exo 20:16; Deu 5:20; \xo e \xt Exo 20:12; Deu 5:16.\x*\wj You know \+add God's\+add* commandsВҰ30767: don't murderВҰ30773, don't commitВҰ30775 adulteryВҰ30775, don't stealВҰ30777, don't lie about others, don't defraudВҰ30782 others, andВҰ30788 honourВҰ30784 yourВҰ30787 parents.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 20 The man responded, вҖңI've keptВҰ30803 all of those since I was young.вҖқ
\p
\v 21 \nd Yeshua\nd* looked up at him with genuine love and saidВҰ30821, вҖң\wj There's one thing still to be done: sell everything you have and giveВҰ30837 the money to the poorвҖ”thenВҰ30813 you'll have wealth in heavenВҰ30844. After that, comeВҰ30847 and followВҰ30848 me.\wj*вҖқ
\v 22 But the man grew very sad when he heard this, becauseВҰ30876 he owned many propertiesВҰ30878.
\p
\v 23 \nd Yeshua\nd* lookedВҰ30882 aroundВҰ30882 at hisВҰ30889 followers, вҖң\wj It's so difficultВҰ30891 for wealthyВҰ30894 people to enter God's kingdomВҰ30898.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 24 (HisВҰ30910 followers were a bit stunned at hisВҰ30910 teaching.) \nd Yeshua\nd* continued, вҖң\wj Yes, it's certainly difficultВҰ30921 to enter into God's kingdomВҰ30930.\wj*
\v 25 \wj It's easierВҰ30935 for a camelВҰ30939 to go through the eyeВҰ30943 of a needleВҰ30947 than for a rich person to enter God's kingdomВҰ30956.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 26 Now theyВҰ30961 were totally stunned, asking, вҖңHow can anyone possibly be savedВҰ30973 thenВҰ30969?вҖқ
\p
\v 27 \nd Yeshua\nd* looked intently at them, вҖң\wj Yes, humanlyВҰ30983 it's quite impossibleВҰ30985. But with God it's differentвҖ”God can do anything!\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 28 PeterВҰ31005 saidВҰ31003, вҖңWe left everything and came and followedВҰ31014 youВҰ31016.вҖқ
\p
\v 29 He answered, вҖң\wj Yes I can assure youВҰ31031 all that anyoneВҰ31033 who left their home or farm, and left their siblings or parents or childrenВҰ31051 because of me and myВҰ31055 teaching,\wj*
\v 30 \wj they'll be rewarded one hundredВҰ31067 times over with homes and farmsВҰ31090 and siblings and parents and childrenВҰ31088 along with persecutionВҰ31092, butВҰ31078 gaining eternalВҰ31101 lifeВҰ31100 in the next era.\wj*
\v 31 \x + \xo 10:31: \xt Mat 20:16; Luk 13:30.\x*\wj ButВҰ31108 many at the top now will be at the bottom then, andВҰ31108 many at the bottom now will be blessed then.\wj*вҖқ
\s1 Yeshua predicts his execution a third time
\rem /s1 Jesus Again Predicts His Death; A Third Time Jesus Foretells His Death and Resurrection; Jesus Speaks a Third Time about His Death
\r (Mat. 20:17-19; Luke 18:31-34)
\p
\v 32 They were \add heading south\add* on their wayВҰ31116 to Yerushalem with Yeshua in front, and his followersВҰ31132 were a bit surprised and a bit scared. Yeshua took the twelveВҰ31139 aside and started tellingВҰ31142 them what was going to happenВҰ31146 to him,
\v 33 вҖң\wj We're on our way down to Yerushalem and humanity's child will be turned over to the chiefВҰ31159 priestsВҰ31159 and the religiousВҰ31162 teachersВҰ31162, and they'll sentence him to die and pass him over to the non-Jews.\wj*
\v 34 \wj ThenВҰ31173 they'll ridicule him and spit on him before they beat him and execute him, butВҰ31173 he'll come back to life again in threeВҰ31193 daysВҰ31195 timeВҰ31195.\wj*вҖқ
\s1 How to become respected in God's kingdom
\rem /s1 The Request of James and John; Jesus Teaches about Serving Others
\r (Mat. 20:20-28)
\p
\v 35 ThenВҰ31198 Yacob and Yohan, the twoВҰ31208 sonsВҰ31209 of ZebedeeВҰ31210 approachedВҰ31202 Yeshua and asked, вҖңTeacherВҰ31215, we'd like to ask a favour from youвҖ”please don't disappoint us.вҖқ
\p
\v 36 вҖң\wj What doВҰ31239 you want from me?\wj*вҖқ Yeshua asked.
\p
\v 37 They answered, вҖңAllow us two to sitВҰ31262 beside you in heavenвҖ”one of us on each side of you.вҖқ
\p
\v 38 \x + \xo 10:38: \xt Luk 12:50.\x*ButВҰ31272 \nd Yeshua\nd* replied, вҖң\wj You don'tВҰ31278 even understand what you're asking for. Do you think you could endure the suffering that I have to go through? Or to be enveloped in the darkness that I have to go down into?\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 39 And they replied, вҖңSure we can.вҖқ
\p вҖң\wj And indeed you all will suffer like me andВҰ31299 be enveloped in darkness like I will be,\wj*вҖқ respondedВҰ31300 \nd Yeshua\nd*,
\v 40 вҖң\wj but as for deciding who will sitВҰ31325 next to me, that's not myВҰ31328 decision to make because it's already been decided.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 41 WhenВҰ31346 the tenВҰ31350 other apprentices heardВҰ31347 what these two had asked for, they were upset at Yacob andВҰ31361 Yohan.
\v 42 \x + \xo 10:42-43: \xt Luk 22:25-26.\x*ButВҰ31364 \nd Yeshua\nd* calledВҰ31367 them over, вҖң\wj Listen, in most countries their rulers boss the people around andВҰ31384 their leaders exert their authorityВҰ31390 over them.\wj*
\v 43 \x + \xo 10:43-44: \xt Mat 23:11; Mrk 9:35; Luk 22:26.\x*\wj But itВҰ31396 doesn't work like that with youвҖ”anyone of you who wanted to be honoured mustВҰ31413 serve the others,\wj*
\v 44 \wj andВҰ31418 anyone who wants to become the most respected has to \+add work\+add* like a slaveВҰ31432 does.\wj*
\v 45 \wj Even humanity's child didn'tВҰ31439 come to be servedВҰ31441, butВҰ31442 to serveВҰ31443 others andВҰ31444 to giveВҰ31445 hisВҰ31448 lifeВҰ31447 as a ransomВҰ31450 to set many people free.\wj*вҖқ
\s1 Blind Bartimayos gets his miracle
\rem /s1 Blind Bartimaeus Receives His Sight; The Healing of Blind Bartimaeus; Jesus Heals Blind Bartimaeus
\r (Mat. 20:29-34; Luke 18:35-43)
\p
\v 46 They arrived at Jericho, and thenВҰ31453 when Yeshua and hisВҰ31468 followers were leaving again with a largeВҰ31471 crowdВҰ31470 following, theyВҰ31454 came across blindВҰ31477 BartimayosВҰ31475 sittingВҰ31480 besideВҰ31481 the pathВҰ31483 begging.
\v 47 WhenВҰ31486 he heardВҰ31487 that it was Yeshua from \nd NazarethВҰ31493\nd* going past, he yelled out, вҖңYeshua, \add promised\add* descendant of DavidВҰ31501, help me please.вҖқ
\p
\v 48 WhenВҰ31505 several people told him to stop, he just yelled out even louder, вҖңYeshua, \add promised\add* descendant of DavidВҰ31522, please help me.вҖқ
\p
\v 49 ThenВҰ31525 \nd Yeshua\nd* stoppedВҰ31526 and got the people to call the blindВҰ31540 manВҰ31540. SoВҰ31525 they called him, вҖңHey, be confident! Get up and come because he's called for you.вҖқ
\p
\v 50 SoВҰ31551 Bartimayos threw off hisВҰ31555 jacket, jumpedВҰ31556 up, andВҰ31551 was led to \nd Yeshua\nd*.
\p
\v 51 вҖң\wj Now, what can I doВҰ31573 for you?\wj*вҖқ \nd Yeshua\nd* asked.
\p вҖңMy teacherВҰ31582, I'd like to be able to see,вҖқ Bartimayos replied.
\p
\v 52 ThenВҰ31587 Yeshua respondedВҰ31589, вҖң\wj Okay, off you go thenВҰ31587вҖ”yourВҰ31594 faithВҰ31593 has savedВҰ31595 you.\wj*вҖқ
\p And immediatelyВҰ31598 Bartimayos was able to see, andВҰ31587 followedВҰ31601 along the pathВҰ31607 afterВҰ31602 Yeshua.
\c 11
\s1 Yeshua is treated like a king as he enters Yerushalem
\rem /s1 The Triumphant Entry into Jerusalem; Jesus' Triumphal Entry into Jerusalem; The challenge to Jerusalem
\r (Yhn 12:12-19; Mat. 21:1-11; Luke 19:28-40)
\p
\v 1 As theyВҰ31610 got close to Yerushalem and were passing BethphageВҰ31616 and BethanyВҰ31619 on the MtВҰ31622. of OlivesВҰ31625, Yeshua sent twoВҰ31628 of hisВҰ31631 apprenticesВҰ31630 ahead, telling them,
\v 2 вҖң\wj Go on to the next villageВҰ31641 and as you enterВҰ31647 it, you'll see a young donkey thatВҰ31642 hasn't ever been ridden yet. Untie it and bringВҰ31671 it back here.\wj*
\v 3 \wj If anyoneВҰ31676 asks what you're doingВҰ31681, tell them that the \+nd masterВҰ31689\+nd* needs it andВҰ31673 he'll return it later.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 4 SoВҰ31702 they went ahead and foundВҰ31707 a donkey tied up on the path just outsideВҰ31716 the doorВҰ31713 of a house, and so they went to untie it.
\v 5 ButВҰ31723 some of the people standing around thereВҰ31727 saidВҰ31729, вҖңHoy! What do you think you're doingВҰ31732 untying that donkey?вҖқ
\p
\v 6 SoВҰ31737 they responded just as \nd YeshuaВҰ31746\nd* had told them, andВҰ31737 the people allowedВҰ31748 them to proceed.
\v 7 They brought the young donkey to Yeshua, placing theirВҰ31767 coatsВҰ31765 over it before Yeshua mounted it.
\v 8 \add As Yeshua rode it into Yerushalem,\add* many people laid theirВҰ31783 coatsВҰ31781 on the roadВҰ31790, while othersВҰ31792 lay down leafyВҰ31794 branchesВҰ31794 cut from trees in nearby fieldsВҰ31799.
\v 9 \x + \xo 11:9: \xt Psa 118:25-26.\x*Some went ahead and others came along behind, shouting, вҖңThis is the saviourВҰ31815 who comes with the authority and blessingВҰ31816 from \nd YahwehВҰ31821\nd*вҖ”
\v 10 the promised ancestor of King DavidВҰ31833 who is blessed as he ushers in his kingdomВҰ31826вҖ”the blessed saviourВҰ31834 from heaven.вҖқ
\p
\v 11 And so Yeshua arrived in Yerushalem and went into the templeВҰ31849 and lookedВҰ31851 all aroundВҰ31851, butВҰ31839 because it was now eveningВҰ31853, he went back out to Bethania village with his twelveВҰ31864 apprentices.
\s1 Yeshua curses a fig tree
\rem /s1 Jesus Clears the Temple; Jesus Curses the Fig Tree
\r (Mat. 21:18-19)
\p
\v 12 The next dayВҰ31867 after they'd left Bethania, Yeshua was hungry.
\v 13 From a distance he noticed a figВҰ31881 treeВҰ31881 that was in leaf so he wentВҰ31888 over to see if there was any fruit on it, butВҰ31879 when he reached it there was only leaves becauseВҰ31922 it wasn't the right seasonВҰ31925 for figsВҰ31929.
\v 14 SoВҰ31930 he spoke to the tree, вҖң\wj No one in this age will ever eatВҰ31956 fruitВҰ31954 from you again.\wj*вҖқ (HisВҰ31963 followers heard him say that.)
\s1 Yeshua upsets the traders inside the temple
\rem /s1 Jesus Goes to the Temple; Jesus Cleanses the Temple; Jesus Clears the Temple
\r (Yhn 2:13-22; Mat. 21:12-17; Luke 19:45-48)
\p
\v 15 Then they came back into Yerushalem and on into the temple where Yeshua started drivingВҰ31983 out the sellers and the buyers that were trading in there. Then he tipped over the tablesВҰ31997 of the money-changers and the chairs of the ones selling dovesВҰ32008,
\v 16 andВҰ32012 stopped others from carryingВҰ32017 goods through the templeВҰ32024.
\v 17 \x + \xo 11:17: a \xt Isa 56:7; \xo b \xt Jer 7:11.\x*He saidВҰ32029, вҖң\wj Isn't it writtenВҰ32032 in the Scriptures,\wj*
\q1 \wj вҖҳMyВҰ32036 house will be known as a house of prayerВҰ32038 for all the nationsВҰ32042вҖҷ?\wj*
\m \wj ButВҰ32025 all of you have turned it into a sanctuary for swindlers.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 18 WhenВҰ32052 the chiefВҰ32055 priestsВҰ32055 and the religiousВҰ32059 teachersВҰ32059 heardВҰ32053 this, they started lookingВҰ32062 forВҰ32062 a way that they could destroyВҰ32065 him, because they were afraid of him and the way that the crowdВҰ32074 marvelled at hisВҰ32080 teaching.
\p
\v 19 Every eveningВҰ32084, Yeshua andВҰ32081 his apprentices would go out of the cityВҰ32092 to stay overnight.
\s1 Yeshua gives a lesson on moving mountains
\rem /s1 The Lesson from the Fig Tree; The Withered Fig Tree; The Lesson from the Withered Fig Tree
\r (Mat. 21:20-22)
\p
\v 20 As theyВҰ32101 entered the city again in the morningВҰ32099, Yeshua's apprentices noticedВҰ32101 that the figВҰ32103 treeВҰ32103 was totally dead.
\v 21 PeterВҰ32110 remembered what he had saidВҰ32111 to the tree, andВҰ32107 commented, вҖңTeacherВҰ32113, that figВҰ32117 tree that you cursedВҰ32119 has witheredВҰ32120 up.вҖқ
\p
\v 22 \nd Yeshua\nd* responded, вҖң\wj Use your faithВҰ32130 in \+nd GodВҰ32132\+nd*.\wj*
\v 23 \x + \xo 11:23: \xt Mat 17:20; 1Cor 13:2.\x*\wj I can assure youВҰ32136 that if anyone tells a mountainВҰ32143 to go into the seaВҰ32152 and doesn't doubtВҰ32155 in their mindВҰ32159 butВҰ32147 believesВҰ32163 that what they're sayingВҰ32135 will happen, then itВҰ32155 will.\wj*
\v 24 \wj So I tell you all that anything you ask God for in your prayers, if you believeВҰ32192 that you have receivedВҰ32194 itВҰ32199, then you will.\wj*
\v 25 \x + \xo 11:25-26: \xt Mat 6:14-15.\x*\wj Whenever you are standingВҰ32205 prayingВҰ32206, if you have something againstВҰ32215 someoneВҰ32216, be sure to forgive them so that your fatherВҰ32220 in heavenВҰ32226 can also forgive your shortcomings.\wj*вҖқ
\s1 The leaders question Yeshua's authority
\rem /s1 The Authority of Jesus Challenged; The Authority of Jesus Questioned; The Question about Jesus' Authority
\r (Mat. 21:23-27; Luke 20:1-8)
\p
\v 26 в—ҳ
\rem /s1 Jesus' Authority Is Questioned
\v 27 They continued on into Yerushalem and on to the templeВҰ32261 where theyВҰ32253 were met by the chiefВҰ32268 priestsВҰ32268 and the religiousВҰ32271 teachersВҰ32271 and the eldersВҰ32274.
\v 28 They asked Yeshua, вҖңDo you have any authority to do what you did? If so, who gave it to you?вҖқ
\p
\v 29 \nd Yeshua\nd* answered, вҖң\wj Okay, I'll also ask you something andВҰ32301 when you answerВҰ32316 me I'll tell you about my authorityВҰ32326 to do that:\wj*
\v 30 \wj When Yohan \+add preached and\+add* immersedВҰ32330 people, did the authority for thatВҰ32331 come from heavenВҰ32337 or from people here?\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 31 They discussed this among themselvesВҰ32351, reasoningВҰ32347, вҖңIf we sayВҰ32357 it was from heavenВҰ32359, he'll ask us why we didn'tВҰ32367 believeВҰ32368 himВҰ32369.
\v 32 But weВҰ32372 can't sayВҰ32372 that it was just from people.вҖқ (They said that becauseВҰ32383 they were scared of the crowdsВҰ32379, knowing that they believed that Yohan was a prophetВҰ32392.)
\v 33 SoВҰ32394 theyВҰ32399 answeredВҰ32395, вҖңWe don'tВҰ32400 know.вҖқ
\p And \nd Yeshua\nd* also responded, вҖң\wj Well thenВҰ32394, I won'tВҰ32400 tell youВҰ32413 about my authorityВҰ32418 to do those things either.\wj*вҖқ
\c 12
\s1 The parable about the tenants killing the owner's son
\rem /s1 The Parable of the Wicked Tenants; Story of the Evil Farmers; The Parable of the Tenants in the Vineyard
\r (Mat. 21:33-46; Luke 20:9-19)
\p
\v 1 \x + \xo 12:1: \xt Isa 5:1-2.\x*Then he started telling them some parablesВҰ32426: вҖң\wj A manВҰ32431 plantedВҰ32433 a vineyardВҰ32429 and put a fenceВҰ32438 and a moat aroundВҰ32436 it and builtВҰ32444 a \+add security\+add* towerВҰ32445. Then he rentedВҰ32447 it out and went off travellingВҰ32452.\wj*
\v 2 \wj At harvest time, he sent a slaveВҰ32460 to go to the tenant farmers andВҰ32453 get his \+add percentage\+add* of the harvest.\wj*
\v 3 \wj ButВҰ32484 the tenants grabbed the slave and beat him up, then sentВҰ32485 him back empty-handed.\wj*
\v 4 \wj The owner sentВҰ32491 a second slaveВҰ32495, butВҰ32489 theyВҰ32500 insulted this one andВҰ32489 struckВҰ32500 him on the headВҰ32500.\wj*
\v 5 \wj SoВҰ32506 the owner sent a third slave and they murdered him. He sent many other slavesвҖ”some they just beat up and others they murdered.\wj*
\v 6 \wj But the owner stillВҰ32527 had his one, dearly loved son, so finally he sentВҰ32539 him to go, thinking that they would now be convinced because it was his son.\wj*
\v 7 \wj ButВҰ32573 the tenantВҰ32557 farmersВҰ32557 saidВҰ32564 to each others, вҖҳAh ha. This is the one who will inheritВҰ32577 this land. If we killВҰ32571 \+em himВҰ32572\+em*, we'll be the ones to control the estate.вҖҷ\wj*
\v 8 \wj SoВҰ32578 they took him and killedВҰ32581 him, and threw the body outsideВҰ32586 the vineyardВҰ32588 fence.\wj*
\p
\v 9 вҖң\wj Now, what do you think the owner of the vineyard will do? Yes, he'll come and eliminate those \+add evil\+add* tenantsВҰ32600, and give the contract to othersВҰ32605.\wj*
\v 10 \x + \xo 12:10-11: \xt Psa 118:22-23.\x*\wj Haven'tВҰ32612 you all read this in the scripturesВҰ32608:\wj*
\q1 \wj вҖҳthe stoneВҰ32612 thatВҰ32613 the buildersВҰ32616 rejectedВҰ32614\wj*
\q1 \wj became the \+add important\+add* cornerstoneВҰ32621\wj*
\q1
\v 11 \wj that was given by \+nd YahwehВҰ32623\+nd*,\wj*
\q1 \wj andВҰ32626 we think it's incredible.вҖҷ?\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 12 And those leaders tried to arrest him because they knewВҰ32640 that it was them that the parableВҰ32646 was addressed to, butВҰ32632 they couldn't do it because \add Yeshua had the favour\add* of the crowdВҰ32639, so they just left the area.
\s1 Yeshua answers about payment of taxes
\rem /s1 Paying Taxes to Caesar; The Question about Paying Taxes; Taxes for Caesar
\r (Mat. 22:15-22; Luke 20:20-26)
\p
\v 13 ThenВҰ32654 the religious leaders sent some members of the Pharisee partyВҰ32660 andВҰ32661 some of the \add political\add* supportersВҰ32663 of King HerodВҰ32663 to try to catchВҰ32667 Yeshua out.
\v 14 SoВҰ32670 they \add flattered\add* him, вҖңTeacherВҰ32683, we know that you are honest even if it upsets others, andВҰ32670 that you teachВҰ32707 the truthВҰ32702 about \nd GodВҰ32706\nd* without caringВҰ32690 about people'sВҰ32699 opinions. Is it legal \add for us Jews\add* to pay the poll taxВҰ32717 to the Roman emperor or not? How should we handle this?вҖқ
\p
\v 15 ButВҰ32728 knowingВҰ32731 theirВҰ32732 hypocrisyВҰ32734, Yeshua respondedВҰ32735 to them, вҖң\wj Why are youВҰ32739 trying to test me? Bring me a coin so we can determine the proper answer.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 16 WhenВҰ32749 they broughtВҰ32750 him a coin, he asked, вҖң\wj Whose imageВҰ32756 andВҰ32749 inscriptionВҰ32760 are on this coin?\wj*вҖқ
\p And they saidВҰ32763, вҖңThe emperor's.вҖқ
\p
\v 17 вҖң\wj Well thenВҰ32770,\wj*вҖқ said \nd Yeshua\nd*, вҖң\wj give to the emperor whatever is due him, butВҰ32770 give God what is owed to God.\wj*вҖқ
\p And they had to admit that that was an outstanding answer.
\s1 Yeshua explains that those who've died are alive
\rem /s1 The Question about Rising from Death; Discussion about Resurrection; The Question about the Resurrection; Marriage at the Resurrection
\r (Mat. 22:23-33; Luke 20:27-40)
\p
\v 18 \x + \xo 12:18: \xt Acts 23:8.\x*Another time, members of the Sadducee sect came to Yeshua andВҰ32806 asked,
\v 19 \x + \xo 12:19: \xt Deu 25:5.\x*вҖңTeacherВҰ32811, Mosheh wroteВҰ32813 that if a man's married brother should die before his wife without having any childrenВҰ32834, then his brother should marry her to produce descendants in his brother's name.
\v 20 Now what if there were sevenВҰ32854 brothersВҰ32856 and the firstВҰ32863 one got married and died childless.
\v 21 So then the secondВҰ32875 brother tookВҰ32876 herВҰ32877 in, butВҰ32873 again diedВҰ32879 childless, and then the thirdВҰ32890.
\v 22 Eventually all sevenВҰ32899 brothers died childless, and finally the womanВҰ32911 also died.
\v 23 Now, at the resurrectionВҰ32916 of the dead, whichВҰ32920 brother will she be the wife of, becauseВҰ32927 at some point, she was married to each of the sevenВҰ32928 of them?вҖқ
\p
\v 24 So \nd Yeshua\nd* answered, вҖң\wj Actually you're all quite wrong, because you ignore the scripturesВҰ32949 and also because you haven't experienced God's powerВҰ32952.\wj*
\v 25 \wj When the deadВҰ32959 do come back to life, they won't be getting engaged or married, but will be like the messengersВҰ32974 in heavenВҰ32978.\wj*
\v 26 \x + \xo 12:26: \xt Exo 3:6.\x*\wj And as for the state of those who've died, didn'tВҰ32986 you read in the scriptures about Mosheh when \+nd GodВҰ33004\+nd* spokeВҰ33001 to him in front of the \+add burning\+add* thornВҰ32997 bush and saidВҰ33005, вҖҳI \+em am\+em* the god of AbrahamВҰ33010 and the god of IsaacВҰ33014 and the god of YacobВҰ33018вҖҷ?\wj*
\v 27 \wj So \+nd GodВҰ33022\+nd* is not the \+nd godВҰ33022\+nd* of the deadВҰ33023, butВҰ33024 of the livingВҰ33026. You Sadducees are very wrong!\wj*вҖқ
\s1 Yeshua answers about genuine obedience to God
\rem /s1 The Most Important Commandment; The Great Commandment; The Greatest Commandment; The First Commandment
\r (Mat. 22:34-40; Luke 10:25-28)
\p
\v 28 ThenВҰ33031 one of the religiousВҰ33036 teachersВҰ33036 who had heardВҰ33037 theirВҰ33039 question and Yeshua's excellent answerВҰ33048, came closer and askedВҰ33050, вҖңWhichВҰ33054 of \add God's\add* commandsВҰ33056 is the most important?вҖқ
\p
\v 29 \x + \xo 12:29-30: \xt Deu 6:4-5.\x*\nd Yeshua\nd* answeredВҰ33064, вҖң\wj Well, the most important is this: вҖҳListen, Yisrael. OurВҰ33086 \+nd GodВҰ33085 YahwehВҰ33083\+nd* is \+add &our\+add* master.\wj*
\v 30 \wj You mustВҰ33091 love \+nd YahwehВҰ33092 GodВҰ33094\+nd* with all your heartВҰ33099 and with all your soulВҰ33106 and with all your mindВҰ33099 and with all your strengthВҰ33119.вҖҷ\wj*
\v 31 \x + \xo 12:31: \xt Lev 19:18.\x*\wj And the secondВҰ33125 is: вҖҳLove yourВҰ33136 neighbourВҰ33135 like \+add youВҰ33136 look after\+add* yourselfВҰ33138.вҖҷ There's no other commandsВҰ33143 more important than theseВҰ33141.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 32 \x + \xo 12:32: \xt Deu 4:35.\x*The teacher replied to Yeshua, вҖңYes, teacher, you're quite right saying there'sВҰ33167 only one God andВҰ33165 no other,
\v 33 \x + \xo 12:33: \xt Hos 6:6.\x*and saying thatВҰ33199 we should love him with all our heartВҰ33178 and all our intelligenceВҰ33186 and all our strengthВҰ33197, and to be loving our neighboursВҰ33202 like we \add look after\add* ourselves, and all this is more importantВҰ33207 than all the required temple offeringsВҰ33212 and sacrificesВҰ33215.вҖқ
\p
\v 34 \x + \xo 12:28-34: \xt Luk 10:25-28.\x*WhenВҰ33216 Yeshua saw that he'd given such a thoughtful answerВҰ33223, he saidВҰ33224, вҖң\wj You're very close to \+nd GodВҰ33234's\+nd* kingdomВҰ33232!\wj*вҖқ
\p After that, no one else dared to askВҰ33241 Yeshua any more questions.
\s1 Yeshua asks about the messiah being David's descendant
\rem /s1 Whose Son Is the Messiah?; The Question about the Messiah; Whose Son Is the Christ; The Question about David's Son
\r (Mat. 22:41-46; Luke 20:41-44)
\p
\v 35 Later when \nd Yeshua\nd* was teaching in the templeВҰ33253, he asked the people, вҖң\wj How is it that the teachersВҰ33258 here say that the \+nd messiahВҰ33261\+nd* is a descendant of King DavidВҰ33264?\wj*
\v 36 \x + \xo 12:36: \xt Psa 110:1.\x*\wj Because David himselfВҰ33267 said under the inspiration of the holy \+nd spiritВҰ33274\+nd*,\wj*
\q1 \wj вҖҳThe \+nd master\+nd* told myВҰ33283 \+nd master\+nd*,\wj*
\q2 \wj вҖңSit there in the position of honour\wj*
\q2 \wj untilВҰ33289 I can conquer yourВҰ33295 enemiesВҰ33294.вҖқ вҖҷ\wj*
\m
\v 37 \wj If David calls \+add @the messiah\+add* hisВҰ33311 \+nd masterВҰ33306\+nd*, how can \+add @the messiah\+add* possibly be \+add @David's\+add* descendant?\wj*вҖқ
\p The largeВҰ33317 crowdВҰ33318 was very interested to hearВҰ33320 everything that Yeshua had to say.
\s1 Yeshua warns about well-dressed teachers
\rem /s1 Jesus Warns against the Teachers of the Law; Jesus Denounces the Scribes
\r (Mat. 23:1-36; Luke 20:45-47)
\p
\v 38 As Yeshua continued teaching, he saidВҰ33337, вҖң\wj Watch out for these religiousВҰ33341 teachersВҰ33341 who like to wear \+add fancy\+add* robesВҰ33348 andВҰ33328 be greetedВҰ33351 in the square,\wj*
\v 39 \wj and have the best seatsВҰ33357 at meetings and the best placesВҰ33362 at dinners.\wj*
\v 40 \wj TheseВҰ33380 people trick widowsВҰ33372 out of their properties, butВҰ33373 offer longВҰ33377 prayers to cover it up. They will be getting a stricter judgementВҰ33384 than others.\wj*вҖқ
\s1 The sacrificial donation of a widow
\rem /s1 The Widow's Offering
\r (Luke 21:1-4)
\p
\v 41 As he satВҰ33386 down in frontВҰ33390 of the \add temple\add* treasury, Yeshua watched the crowdВҰ33402 as they threw coins into \add the dish\add*, andВҰ33385 some rich people were donating quite valuable \add silver\add* coins.
\v 42 ThenВҰ33415 an impoverished widowВҰ33421 came andВҰ33415 threw in twoВҰ33425 small \add copper\add* coins.
\v 43 Yeshua calledВҰ33430 hisВҰ33433 followers andВҰ33429 told them, вҖң\wj Honestly, that poor widowВҰ33442 gave more than all the others.\wj*
\v 44 \wj You see, most people donate from their excess wealthВҰ33463, butВҰ33470 this womanВҰ33469 even gave \+add some of\+add* the small amount that sheВҰ33477 needed to live on.\wj*вҖқ
\c 13
\s1 Yeshua predicts total destruction of the temple
\rem /s1 Warnings about the end; Jesus Speaks of the Destruction of the Temple; The Destruction of the Temple Foretold; Signs of the End of the Age; Jesus Foretells the Future
\r (Mat. 24:1-2; Luke 21:5-6)
\p
\v 1 As they were leaving the templeВҰ33488 area, one of Yeshua's followers noted, вҖңTeacherВҰ33498, look at those \add large, chiselled\add* stonesВҰ33501 andВҰ33502 the \add beautiful\add* buildingsВҰ33504 \add that they've been made into\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 2 ButВҰ33507 \nd Yeshua\nd* respondedВҰ33512, вҖң\wj Yes, incredible buildingsВҰ33522, butВҰ33507 \+add the time will come\+add* when they're torn downвҖ”not a single \+add piece of\+add* stoneВҰ33533 will be left sitting in its place.\wj*вҖқ
\s1 Yeshua talks about coming hardships
\rem /s1 Troubles and Persecutions
\r (Mat. 24:3-14; Luke 21:7-19)
\p
\v 3 Later when they were over on the MountВҰ33557 of OlivesВҰ33559 overlooking the templeВҰ33562, PeterВҰ33569 and Yacob and Yohan and AndrewВҰ33575 were with Yeshua and asked
\v 4 when all this destruction would happen, andВҰ33581 what indications there would be that it would be about to happen.
\p
\v 5 SoВҰ33597 \nd Yeshua\nd* told them, вҖң\wj Be careful so youВҰ33609 aren't misledВҰ33610 by others.\wj*
\v 6 \wj Plenty of people will say that they're comingВҰ33614 \+add вүҲbecause they were sent by me\+add*, or that they \+em are\+em* me, and they'll misleadВҰ33628 many others.\wj*
\v 7 \wj And wheneverВҰ33629 youВҰ33631 hearВҰ33631 about wars or about battles about to begin, don'tВҰ33638 be worriedвҖ”those things will certainly happen, butВҰ33643 there's more to follow.\wj*
\v 8 \wj Countries will take up arms against other countries, and kingdoms against other kingdoms. There'llВҰ33657 be earthquakesВҰ33658 in \+add many\+add* placesВҰ33660 and there'llВҰ33662 be faminesВҰ33663, butВҰ33652 those will be just like the beginningВҰ33667 of birthВҰ33668 painsВҰ33668.\wj*
\rem /s1 Persecution Foretold
\p
\v 9 \x + \xo 13:9-11: \xt Mat 10:17-20; Luk 12:11-12.\x*вҖң\wj So be careful. You'll be turned over to \+add local\+add* councilsВҰ33683 \+add for questioning\+add*, will be whipped in the religious meetingВҰ33686 hallsВҰ33686, and will be stoodВҰ33696 in front of governorsВҰ33691 and kingsВҰ33695 becauseВҰ33701 of following me. ButВҰ33684 you'll be able to present your life stories to them\wj*
\v 10 \wj andВҰ33704 it's right that the goodВҰ33718 news first\wj*\f + \fr 13:10 \ft TD: It's not clear here what was meant by вҖҳfirstвҖҷвҖ”вҖҳfirstвҖҷ before what?\f* \wj be proclaimedВҰ33716 to every people group.\wj*
\v 11 \wj But wheneverВҰ33724 they bringВҰ33726 you along to hand you over, don'tВҰ33730 worryВҰ33731 in advance about what you're going to say to defend yourselves, but wait until the hearing proceeds and speak what you are givenВҰ33740 then, becauseВҰ33752 then it won'tВҰ33730 be you speaking, but God's \+nd spiritВҰ33759\+nd*.\wj*
\v 12 \wj In those times, a brother will report on his brother to have him executed, and a fatherВҰ33770 report on his child, and children will be encouraged to report on their own parentsВҰ33778 and thenВҰ33762 they'll be executed as a result.\wj*
\v 13 \x + \xo 13:13: \xt Mat 10:22.\x*\wj And every one will hate youВҰ33783 all becauseВҰ33787 they hate myВҰ33790 nameВҰ33789, butВҰ33792 anyone who enduresВҰ33793 to the endВҰ33795 will be savedВҰ33797.\wj*
\s1 Yeshua warns about coming horror and deceptions
\rem /s1 The Desolating Sacrilege; The Awful Horror
\r (Mat. 24:15-28; Luke 21:20-24)
\p
\v 14 \x + \xo 13:14: \xt Dan 9:27; 11:31; 12:11.\x*вҖң\wj But wheneverВҰ33798 you seeВҰ33801 the most horrible thing that drives people from God, standing whereВҰ33817 itВҰ33819 shouldn'tВҰ33818 be (and you readers should understandВҰ33822 this), then anyone in YudeaВҰ33829 should flee into the hills\wj*
\v 15 \x + \xo 13:15-16: \xt Luk 17:31.\x*\wj and anyone upstairs looking outside shouldn'tВҰ33840 come down into the bedrooms to get anythingВҰ33849,\wj*
\v 16 \wj andВҰ33855 anyone working outside shouldn'tВҰ33861 go back inside to get a change of clothes.\wj*
\v 17 \wj It will be extremely difficult for pregnant women and for mothers who are breast-feeding their childrenВҰ33877 in thoseВҰ33883 daysВҰ33885.\wj*
\v 18 \wj Just pray that itВҰ33891 won'tВҰ33890 happen in the winterВҰ33895\wj*
\v 19 \x + \xo 13:19: \xt Dan 12:1; Rev 7:14.\x*\wj becauseВҰ33898 thoseВҰ33901 daysВҰ33900 will be terrible like nothing that's ever happened before, all the way back to when \+nd GodВҰ33918\+nd* createdВҰ33913 the world right untilВҰ33919 the present timeВҰ33920, andВҰ33923 won'tВҰ33906 ever happen again.\wj*
\v 20 \wj And if \+nd YahwehВҰ33933\+nd* hadn't shortened that time, no humans wouldВҰ33941 even survive, butВҰ33945 he shortened that time so that the chosenВҰ33949 ones could be savedВҰ33942.\wj*
\p
\v 21 \wj SoВҰ33956 don'tВҰ33974 believeВҰ33975 itВҰ33975 if youВҰ33961 hear someoneВҰ33960 sayВҰ33962, вҖҳLookВҰ33964, the \+nd messiahВҰ33968\+nd* has arrived here.вҖҷ or вҖҳThere's the one that God has sent.вҖҷ\wj*
\v 22 \wj Plenty of fake messiahsВҰ33981 and deceiving prophetsВҰ33983 will certainly come and even do things that humans can't normally do, so much so that even the chosenВҰ33998 ones would defect if that were possibleВҰ33995.\wj*
\v 23 \wj So watchВҰ34001 out, butВҰ34000 I'veВҰ34003 warned you in advance about all of this.\wj*
\s1 The universe collapses as the son arrives
\rem /s1 The Coming of the Son of Man
\r (Mat. 24:29-31; Luke 21:25-28)
\p
\v 24 \x + \xo 13:24: a \xt Isa 13:10; Yoel 2:10,31; 3:15; Rev 6:12; \xo b \xt Isa 13:10; Eze 32:7.\x*вҖң\wj After thoseВҰ34009 very difficult times, the sunВҰ34017 will go dark andВҰ34019 the moonВҰ34021 won'tВҰ34022 shine at night.\wj*
\v 25 \x + \xo 13:25: a \xt Isa 34:4; Rev 6:13; \xo b \xt Yoel 2:10.\x*\wj The starsВҰ34029 will fall down out of the skyВҰ34034 and the powersВҰ34041 in the heavensВҰ34047 will be shakenВҰ34050 up.\wj*
\v 26 \x + \xo 13:26: \xt Dan 7:13; Rev 1:7.\x*\wj ThenВҰ34051 the people will see humanity's child in the cloudsВҰ34062 comingВҰ34058 with incredible powerВҰ34066 andВҰ34068 brightness.\wj*
\v 27 \wj He'll send the messengersВҰ34076 out to collect all the chosenВҰ34082 people from the fourВҰ34086 corners of the world, from everywhere between the earthВҰ34092 andВҰ34078 the sky.\wj*
\s1 Watch out for the change in season
\rem /s1 The Lesson of the Fig Tree
\r (Mat. 24:32-35; Luke 21:29-33)
\p
\v 28 вҖң\wj SoВҰ34099 learnВҰ34102 a lesson from figВҰ34101 treesвҖ”wheneverВҰ34105 the branchesВҰ34109 green up and start sproutingВҰ34114 leavesВҰ34116 and thenВҰ34099 everyone knows that summerВҰ34125 is close.\wj*
\v 29 \wj So too wheneverВҰ34130 you seeВҰ34132 all theseВҰ34134 things happening, you know that the end \+add of this current world\+add* is close.\wj*
\v 30 \wj I can assure you that the generationВҰ34155 of people who see these things won'tВҰ34152 die off before these latter things happen.\wj*
\v 31 \wj The sky andВҰ34167 the planet might collapse, butВҰ34173 myВҰ34175 teachings will never become irrelevant.\wj*
\s1 Stay alert for the coming of the master
\rem /s1 The Day and Hour Unknown; The Necessity for Watchfulness; No One Knows the Day or Hour
\r (Mat. 24:36-44)
\p
\v 32 \x + \xo 13:32: \xt Mat 24:36.\x*вҖң\wj But as for the date or time when all this will happen, only the fatherВҰ34205 knows thatвҖ”even the son and messengersВҰ34193 don'tВҰ34191 know.\wj*
\v 33 \wj So watch out, observe current events, andВҰ34210 be prayingВҰ34211, becauseВҰ34214 youВҰ34213 won'tВҰ34212 know exactly when all this will happen.\wj*
\v 34 \x + \xo 13:34: \xt Luk 12:36-38.\x*\wj It can all be compared to a manВҰ34229 who was about to leave his houseВҰ34234 and go on a trip. Before he leaves, he gives certain jobs and responsibilities to his various slavesВҰ34240, and instructs his security guard to stay alert.\wj*
\v 35 \wj SoВҰ34257 you all watchВҰ34256 and stay alert, becauseВҰ34260 you don'tВҰ34258 know when the masterВҰ34263 of the houseВҰ34265 might returnвҖ”perhaps one eveningВҰ34268 or at midnightВҰ34271, or at dawn or maybe mid-morning.\wj*
\v 36 \wj You certainly don't want to be caught napping when heВҰ34280 comes.\wj*
\v 37 \wj And what I'm telling youВҰ34287 now, I tell everyone: stay alert andВҰ34286 watchВҰ34292.\wj*вҖқ
\c 14
\s1 The leaders plan to eliminate Yeshua
\rem /s1 The Plot against Jesus; The trial and crucifixion of Jesus; Jesus Anointed at Bethany; The Plot to Kill Jesus
\r (Yhn 11:45-53; Mat. 26:1-5; Luke 22:1-2)
\p
\v 1 \x + \xo 14:1: \xt Exo 12:1-27.\x*Now it was twoВҰ34301 daysВҰ34302 before the Passover Feast and the \it Flat Bread Celebration\it*, and the chiefВҰ34306 priestsВҰ34306 and the religiousВҰ34310 teachersВҰ34310 were trying to figure out how they could have Yeshua set up so they could arrest him and have him executed,
\v 2 but theyВҰ34319 knew that the Feast wouldn't be a good time becauseВҰ34320 the peopleВҰ34332 would protest \add in Yeshua's favour\add*.
\s1 The woman anoints Yeshua for his burial
\rem /s1 Jesus Is Anointed at Bethany; The Anointing at Bethany
\r (Yhn 12:1-8; Mat. 26:6-13)
\p
\v 3 \x + \xo 14:3: \xt Luk 7:37-38.\x*Meanwhile, Yeshua was in BethanyВҰ34339 at the home of SimonВҰ34343 who had previously had leprosyВҰ34345. Yeshua was sittingВҰ34346 there when a womanВҰ34349 cameВҰ34348 in with a hand-crafted container of very expensiveВҰ34357 fragrant oil. Breaking open the sealed flask, sheВҰ34367 pouredВҰ34367 the fragrant oil over Yeshua's headВҰ34372.
\v 4 Immediately some started quietly grumbling about the extravagant waste,
\v 5 thenВҰ34414 theyВҰ34415 scolded the woman becauseВҰ34399 a flask of genuine lotion like this could easily fetch almost a year's wages if it was sold.
\p
\v 6 But \nd Yeshua\nd* spoke up, вҖң\wj What do you think you're doing abusing herвҖ”leave her alone! She'sВҰ34433 done something very goodВҰ34430 for me.\wj*
\v 7 \x + \xo 14:7: \xt Deu 15:11.\x*\wj You'll always have poor people around, and you can help them wheneverВҰ34447 you want to, butВҰ34446 I won'tВҰ34458 be around forever.\wj*
\v 8 \wj She has performed the traditional anointingВҰ34468 of my bodyВҰ34471 in advance of my burialВҰ34475.\wj*
\v 9 \wj And I can assure youВҰ34479 that whereverВҰ34481 the goodВҰ34486 news is proclaimedВҰ34484 around the worldВҰ34491, what she has done today will be part of the story andВҰ34477 she'll be remembered for it.\wj*вҖқ
\s1 Yudas offers to hand Yeshua over
\rem /s1 Judas Agrees to Betray Jesus
\r (Mat. 26:14-16; Luke 22:3-6)
\p
\v 10 ThenВҰ34500 YudasВҰ34503 IscariotВҰ34505, one of Yeshua's twelveВҰ34510 \add apprentices\add*, visited the chiefВҰ34514 priestsВҰ34514 to offer to hand Yeshua over to them.
\v 11 WhenВҰ34523 they heardВҰ34524 this, they were very pleased and promisedВҰ34528 to pay him well, and Yudas asked them about the most convenientВҰ34538 way for them to get hold of Yeshua.
\s1 Yeshua's apprentices prepare the Passover meal
\rem /s1 The Lord's Supper; The Last Supper; The Passover with the Disciples; Jesus Eats the Passover Meal with His Disciples; Communion
\r (Yhn 13:21-30; Mat. 26:17-25; Luke 22:7-14, 21-23)
\p
\v 12 On the firstВҰ34542 dayВҰ34543 of the \it Flat Bread Celebration\it* when the lambs would be slaughtered ready for the special Passover meal, Yeshua's apprenticesВҰ34553 asked him, вҖңWhereВҰ34555 do you want us to get everything ready for our Passover meal?вҖқ
\p
\v 13 SoВҰ34564 Yeshua sent off twoВҰ34567 of them with these instructions, вҖң\wj Go into townВҰ34582 andВҰ34564 a manВҰ34588 carrying a pitcherВҰ34589 of waterВҰ34590 will meet you there. Just followВҰ34592 him\wj*
\v 14 \wj until he goes into a house. ThenВҰ34594 find the ownerВҰ34601 of the house and tell him that the teacherВҰ34604 wants to know the location of the guestroomВҰ34609 whereВҰ34595 he and his apprenticesВҰ34616 can celebrate the Passover meal.\wj*
\v 15 \wj He'll show you a largeВҰ34628, furnishedВҰ34629 roomВҰ34626 upstairsВҰ34626вҖ”that's where you can get everything readyВҰ34631.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 16 SoВҰ34637 the two of them wentВҰ34638 off into the townВҰ34652, and everything happened there exactly as Yeshua had told them, and so they preparedВҰ34660 the special meal there.
\s1 Yeshua shocks his apprentices at the Passover meal
\r (Yhn 13:21-30; Mat. 26:20-30; Luke 22:14-23; 1 Cor. 11:23-25)
\p
\v 17 As the eveningВҰ34664 approached, Yeshua went in for dinner with his twelveВҰ34671 apprentices.
\v 18 \x + \xo 14:18: \xt Psa 41:9.\x*As they were sittingВҰ34673 around eating, he told them, вҖң\wj I'll tell you frankly that one of you eating with me here will hand me over \+add to be arrested\+add*.\wj*вҖқ
\v 19 That upset them, andВҰ34703 several of them individually asked, вҖңSurelyВҰ34710 it couldn't be me?вҖқ
\p
\v 20 ThenВҰ34719 he continuedВҰ34721, вҖң\wj It's one of you twelveВҰ34727вҖ”the one who dips his bread in the sauce at the same time as me.\wj*
\v 21 \wj Indeed it's writtenВҰ34749 \+add in the scriptures\+add* that humanity's child will be arrested, but on the otherВҰ34754 hand, what a tragedy it'll be for the one who hands him overвҖ”in fact it would be betterВҰ34765 for that man if he was never born.\wj*вҖқ
\rem /s1 The Lord's Supper; The Institution of the Lord's Supper; Communion
\rem /r (Matthew 26.26-30; Luke 22.14-20; 1 Corinthians 11.23-25)
\p
\v 22 As they carried on eatingВҰ34776, he took some bread, blessedВҰ34782 \add God\add*, brokeВҰ34785 it apart andВҰ34775 gave a piece to them, saying, вҖң\wj Take this breadвҖ”it's myВҰ34800 bodyВҰ34799.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 23 ThenВҰ34801 he picked up a cup, gaveВҰ34806 thanksВҰ34805 \add to God\add*, andВҰ34801 passed it around so they could each drink from it,
\v 24 \x + \xo 14:24: a \xt Exo 24:8; \xo b \xt Jer 31:31-34.\x*saying, вҖң\wj This is the bloodВҰ34821 of myВҰ34822 contract thatВҰ34827 will be pouredВҰ34831 out for many \+add people\+add*.\wj*
\v 25 \wj I can assure you that I won'tВҰ34843 drink anything made from grapes untilВҰ34852 I drink new juice in God's kingdomВҰ34862.\wj*вҖқ
\rem /s1 Peter's Denial Foretold
\p
\v 26 And after they'd sung some songs, they leftВҰ34867 the town andВҰ34865 wentВҰ34867 across to the MountВҰ34870 of OlivesВҰ34872.
\s1 Yeshua predicts Peters denials
\rem /s1 Jesus Predicts Peter's Denial
\r (Yhn 13:36-38; Mat. 26:31-35; Luke 22:31-34)
\p
\v 27 \x + \xo 14:27: \xt Zech 13:7.\x*ThenВҰ34874 \nd Yeshua\nd* continued his teaching, вҖң\wj All of youВҰ34882 will stumbleВҰ34882 becauseВҰ34891 it's writtenВҰ34892 in the scriptures: вҖҳI'llВҰ34893 strikeВҰ34893 down the shepherdВҰ34895 andВҰ34896 the sheepВҰ34900 will be scatteredВҰ34902.вҖҷ\wj*
\v 28 \x + \xo 14:28: \xt Mat 28:16.\x*\wj But afterВҰ34905 I come back to life, I'llВҰ34911 go on ahead of youВҰ34912 back to GalileeВҰ34915.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 29 ButВҰ34917 PeterВҰ34918 contradicted himВҰ34922, вҖңEven if everyone else stumblesВҰ34928, I won'tВҰ34931!вҖқ
\p
\v 30 And \nd Yeshua\nd* responded, вҖң\wj I can assure you that you'll renounceВҰ34961 me threeВҰ34957 times this very nightВҰ34949, beforeВҰ34951 the roosterВҰ34954 crows early tomorrow morning.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 31 ButВҰ34989 Peter argued forcibly, вҖңEven if I had to dieВҰ34980 with you, I would never disown you!вҖқ
\p And all the others saidВҰ34970 similar things.
\s1 Yeshua, in distress, prays at Gethsemane
\rem /s1 Jesus Prays in Gethsemane
\r (Mat. 26:36-46; Luke 22:39-46)
\p
\v 32 They walked along untilВҰ35011 they came to a piece of land called GethsemaneВҰ35002 where Yeshua told hisВҰ35008 apprenticesВҰ35007 to sit down while he prayed.
\v 33 He took PeterВҰ35017 and Yacob and Yohan further in with him where he stared off in a daze butВҰ35014 was obviously very distressedВҰ35031.
\v 34 He told the three of them, вҖң\wj MyВҰ35040 soulВҰ35039 is deathlyВҰ35042 sad! You guys just stay here andВҰ35045 keep alert.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 35 He went ahead a littleВҰ35050 way, where he knelt on the groundВҰ35058 with his head down andВҰ35047 prayedВҰ35061вҖ”asking if it was possibleВҰ35064 to avoid what was ahead of him.
\v 36 ButВҰ35074 he saidВҰ35075, вҖң\wj Father, I know that you can do anything. Let me avoid this suffering, but yes I do know, it doesn't matter what I wantВҰ35105 but rather what you've \+add planned\+add*.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 37 ThenВҰ35107 he went back andВҰ35107 found the others sleeping. He asked PeterВҰ35116, вҖң\wj SimonВҰ35117, are you asleep? Couldn't you stay awake even for a single hourВҰ35123?\wj*
\v 38 \wj You all need to stay alert and be careful not to give into temptationВҰ35133. I know your spiritsВҰ35136 are enthusiastic on one hand, butВҰ35126 it's still easy to give in to the moment.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 39 ThenВҰ35142 he went further in again andВҰ35142 prayedВҰ35145 as before,
\v 40 but when he returned againВҰ35151, he foundВҰ35154 them all asleep becauseВҰ35159 they were tired, but they couldn't really find any excuse to give.
\p
\v 41 The thirdВҰ35178 time that Yeshua returned, he saidВҰ35180 to them, вҖң\wj Ah, you're all sleepingВҰ35182 again andВҰ35175 having a good rest. It's well earned butВҰ35175 the time has come for humanity's child to be handed over to evil men.\wj*
\v 42 \wj Come onвҖ”get upвҖ”weВҰ35208 need to go! LookВҰ35209, the one who'll hand me over is on his way.\wj*вҖқ
\s1 Yeshua is arrested in the night
\rem /s1 Jesus Arrested; Jesus Is Betrayed and Arrested; The Arrest of Jesus; The Betrayal and Arrest of Jesus
\r (Yhn 18:3-12; Mat. 26:47-56; Luke 22:47-53)
\p
\v 43 Even while Yeshua was stillВҰ35219 speakingВҰ35221, YudasВҰ35224 reached him, followed by a crowdВҰ35234 from the chiefВҰ35243 priestsВҰ35243, the religiousВҰ35247 teachersВҰ35247, and the eldersВҰ35250вҖ”many armed with swordsВҰ35237 and clubsВҰ35239.
\v 44 Yudas had prearranged a signalВҰ35258 with them that anyone who he greeted with a kissВҰ35264, they should grab that person andВҰ35253 lead him away under guard.
\p
\v 45 SoВҰ35275 he walked right up to Yeshua and saidВҰ35281, вҖңMy honoured teacher,вҖқ and greeted him with a kiss.
\v 46 ThenВҰ35290 the others with him grabbed Yeshua andВҰ35290 secured him.
\v 47 ButВҰ35321 one of the ones with Yeshua that was beside himВҰ35323, drew hisВҰ35323 swordВҰ35312 andВҰ35321 struckВҰ35315 a slaveВҰ35318 of the chiefВҰ35320 priestВҰ35320, cutting off the man's earВҰ35325.
\v 48 \nd Yeshua\nd* spoke to the crowd, вҖң\wj Did you all bring swordsВҰ35338 andВҰ35339 clubsВҰ35340 to try to captureВҰ35341 me like you'd chase down a thief?\wj*
\v 49 \x + \xo 14:49: \xt Luk 19:47; 21:37.\x*\wj I was standing there teachingВҰ35351 in the templeВҰ35350 everyВҰ35343 dayВҰ35344 and you could have arrested me, butВҰ35352 it's happened this way to ensure that the what's written in scripturesВҰ35361 will be fulfilledВҰ35359.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 50 Meanwhile, the others who'd been with Yeshua had taken off.
\v 51 One youngВҰ35377 fellow was wearing a single linenВҰ35386 robe, andВҰ35374 when the crowd tried to grab him,
\v 52 it came off \add in the struggle\add* and he ran away stark nakedВҰ35404.
\s1 The mock trial where Yeshua is sentenced to death
\rem /s1 Jesus before the Council; Before the Sanhedrin
\r (Yhn 18:13-14,19-24; Mat. 26:57-68; Luke 22:54-55,63-71)
\p
\v 53 The guards led \nd Yeshua\nd* away to the chief priest's residence, and all the chief priestsВҰ35424 and the eldersВҰ35429 and the religiousВҰ35433 teachersВҰ35433 gathered there also.
\v 54 PeterВҰ35436 followedВҰ35439 along from a distance andВҰ35434 went in as far as the courtyardВҰ35446 of the residence where he joined the servants who were sittingВҰ35452 around the fireВҰ35461 keeping warm.
\v 55 Inside, the chiefВҰ35464 priestsВҰ35464 andВҰ35463 all the councilВҰ35468 were trying to establish a case againstВҰ35470 \nd Yeshua\nd* so he could be sentenced to deathВҰ35478, butВҰ35463 they weren't coming up with anything.
\v 56 Several people were making up charges againstВҰ35488 himВҰ35489, butВҰ35490 none of the accusers' stories agreed with each other.
\p
\v 57 Eventually some of them stoodВҰ35499 up andВҰ35496 offered this falseВҰ35500 charge:
\v 58 \x + \xo 14:58: \xt Yhn 2:19.\x*вҖңWe heardВҰ35508 him say that he would demolish this templeВҰ35517 made by many labourers, and within threeВҰ35523 daysВҰ35524 he'd buildВҰ35528 anotherВҰ35525 one without any helpers.вҖқ
\v 59 ButВҰ35529 even thenВҰ35529, they couldn't get theirВҰ35537 accusations to align with each other.
\p
\v 60 Nevertheless the chiefВҰ35541 priestВҰ35541 in the middle of the council stoodВҰ35539 up andВҰ35538 askedВҰ35545 \nd Yeshua\nd*, вҖңAren't you going to defend yourself? These menВҰ35554 are accusing you of theseВҰ35554 things.вҖқ
\p
\v 61 ButВҰ35564 Yeshua didn'tВҰ35565 say anything. So the chiefВҰ35573 priestВҰ35573 asked again, вҖңIs it true that you're the \nd chosenВҰ35587\nd* one that God promised to sendвҖ”the son of the blessedВҰ35593 \add God\add*?вҖқ
\p
\v 62 \x + \xo 14:62: \xt Dan 7:13.\x*\nd Yeshua\nd* replied, вҖңI am. And youВҰ35605 will all see humanity's child sittingВҰ35613 in the honoured position by the powerfulВҰ35615 God andВҰ35616 comingВҰ35617 through the cloudsВҰ35621 in the skyВҰ35624.вҖқ
\p
\v 63 ThenВҰ35626 the chiefВҰ35627 priestВҰ35627 tore his own robe \add to show his disgust\add* andВҰ35626 shouted, вҖңWe certainly don't need any more witnessesВҰ35639 now!
\v 64 \x + \xo 14:64: \xt Lev 24:16.\x*You yourselves all heardВҰ35642 himВҰ35662 insult God. What sentence does that deserve?вҖқ
\p SoВҰ35658 the leaders there agreed that Yeshua needed to be sentenced to deathВҰ35667.
\p
\v 65 ThenВҰ35668 various people started spittingВҰ35671 on him, and blindfoldingВҰ35674 him and beatingВҰ35682 him sayingВҰ35686, вҖңHa, tell us who that was!вҖқ Even the servants joined in to slap him.
\s1 Peter disowns Yeshua
\rem /s1 Peter Denies Jesus
\r (Yhn 18:15-18,25-27; Mat. 26:69-75; Luke 22:56-62)
\p
\v 66 Meanwhile, PeterВҰ35709 was down in the courtyardВҰ35713 when one of the chiefВҰ35723 priest'sВҰ35723 servantВҰ35720 girlsВҰ35720 came out,
\v 67 and seeing PeterВҰ35727 warmingВҰ35728 himselfВҰ35728, sheВҰ35732 looked more closely and saidВҰ35732, вҖңHey, you were with that \nd Yeshua\nd* from \nd NazarethВҰ35740\nd*!вҖқ
\p
\v 68 ButВҰ35760 he denied it, вҖңI don't know him andВҰ35760 I don't know why you think I would!вҖқ And he moved away from the fire.
\p
\v 69 ButВҰ35775 the girlВҰ35777 that had seenВҰ35778 himВҰ35779 saidВҰ35789 to some of the others standing around, вҖңThat guy's one of them.вҖқ
\p
\v 70 ButВҰ35805 again PeterВҰ35814 denied it.
\p A littleВҰ35807 while later, some of those standing there saidВҰ35812, вҖңYou must be one of them becauseВҰ35820 you'reВҰ35818 from GalileeВҰ35821.вҖқ
\p
\v 71 Now Peter started swearingВҰ35834 and cursingВҰ35831 and said, вҖңI'veВҰ35837 never even met that fellow that you're all talkingВҰ35842 about!вҖқ
\p
\v 72 Right thenВҰ35843 the rooster crowed for the secondВҰ35846 timeВҰ35846 and PeterВҰ35853 remembered now what Yeshua had told himвҖ”how he would renounceВҰ35876 Yeshua threeВҰ35874 times before the rooster crowedвҖ”and he brokeВҰ35879 down and cried.
\c 15
\s1 Pilate tries to interrogate Yeshua
\rem /s1 Jesus Before Pilate; Jesus' Trial before Pilate
\r (Yhn 18:28-38; Mat. 27:1-2,11-14; Luke 23:1-5)
\p
\v 1 First thing in the morningВҰ35887, the chiefВҰ35893 priestsВҰ35893 called a meeting with the eldersВҰ35896 and the religiousВҰ35900 teachersВҰ35900 and all the councilВҰ35905, and they ordered that \nd Yeshua\nd* be tied up and taken over to Governor PilateВҰ35919.
\v 2 There PilateВҰ35924 askedВҰ35921 him, вҖңAre you the kingВҰ35929 of the Jews?вҖқ
\p вҖң\wj You saidВҰ35938 itВҰ35940,\wj*вҖқ replied Yeshua.
\p
\v 3 ThenВҰ35941 the chiefВҰ35946 priestsВҰ35946 started hurling accusationsВҰ35942 againstВҰ35944 Yeshua,
\v 4 so PilateВҰ35954 askedВҰ35956 himВҰ35958 again, вҖңDon'tВҰ35961 you have anything to say? ListenВҰ35964 to all these accusationsВҰ35968 they're making against you.вҖқ
\p
\v 5 But PilateВҰ35979 was astounded that \nd Yeshua\nd* didn't answerВҰ35975 any further.
\s1 Pilate agrees to execute an innocent man
\rem /s1 Jesus Is Sentenced to Death; Pilate Hands Jesus over to Be Crucified
\r (Yhn 18:39вҖ“19:16; Mat. 27:15-26; Luke 23:13-25)
\p
\v 6 Now at time of the Jewish Passover, Pilate would normally pardon one prisonerВҰ35991 for them andВҰ35981 release him.
\v 7 There was another prisoner at the time named BarabbasВҰ36003 who was an activist accused of murderВҰ36013.
\v 8 By now, the crowdВҰ36022 had arrived andВҰ36017 asked Pilate to release a prisoner as usual at Passover,
\v 9 so he asked them, вҖңDo you want me to release the KingВҰ36043 of the Jews for you?вҖқ
\v 10 (This was because Pilate was well aware that the chiefВҰ36058 priestsВҰ36058 had brought Yeshua because they were jealous of his \add popularity\add*.)
\v 11 But the chiefВҰ36061 priestsВҰ36061 stirredВҰ36063 up the crowdВҰ36066 to start saying that it was BarabbasВҰ36072 that they wanted released,
\v 12 so PilateВҰ36077 asked againВҰ36078, вҖңThenВҰ36076 what should I doВҰ36087 with this man thatВҰ36088 youВҰ36089 call the KingВҰ36091 of the Jews?вҖқ
\p
\v 13 The crowd yelledВҰ36098 back, вҖңExecuteВҰ36101 himВҰ36102 on a pole.вҖқ
\p
\v 14 вҖңWhat has he even done wrong?вҖқ PilateВҰ36105 demanded.
\p ButВҰ36104 they just yelledВҰ36117 louder, вҖңExecuteВҰ36120 him on a pole!вҖқ
\p
\v 15 Now PilateВҰ36124 wanted to placate the crowdВҰ36127, so he had BarabbasВҰ36138 released while he had \nd Yeshua\nd* floggedВҰ36145 andВҰ36123 thenВҰ36123 handed over to the executionВҰ36148 squad.
\s1 The battalion plays with their mock вҖҳkingвҖҷ
\rem /s1 The Soldiers Make Fun of Jesus; The Soldiers Mock Jesus
\r (Yhn 19:2-3; Mat. 27:27-31)
\p
\v 16 SoВҰ36150 the soldiersВҰ36151 led Yeshua inside the palaceВҰ36158 that was the governor'sВҰ36162 residenceВҰ36162, andВҰ36163 called in the rest of the battalion.
\v 17 They \add mocked Yeshua\add* by dressingВҰ36170 him in a kingly robe, andВҰ36169 after someone twistedВҰ36178 some thornsВҰ36179 togetherВҰ36178 into a mock crownВҰ36180, they pressed it onto his head,
\v 18 andВҰ36181 beganВҰ36182 saluting himВҰ36184, вҖңGreetingsВҰ36187, kingВҰ36190 of the Jews.вҖқ
\v 19 They took turns whacking hisВҰ36195 headВҰ36200 with a stick and spittingВҰ36204 on him, while others knelt down in front of him and pretended to be bowing to him.
\v 20 After they'd finished having fun mocking him, they took the purpleВҰ36220 robe off him, andВҰ36213 put hisВҰ36227 own robe back on him. ThenВҰ36213 they led him outside towards the executionВҰ36235 spot.
\s1 Yeshua is publicly executed along with thieves
\rem /s1 The Crucifixion of Jesus; Jesus Is Crucified
\r (Yhn 19:17-27; Mat. 27:32-44; Luke 23:26-43)
\p
\v 21 \x + \xo 15:21: \xt Rom 16:13.\x*As they walked out of the city, they came across a manВҰ36241 comingВҰ36247 in from the countryВҰ36250. He was SimonВҰ36243 from CyreneВҰ36246, the fatherВҰ36252 of AlexanderВҰ36253 and RufusВҰ36255, and the soldiers forced himВҰ36260 to carryВҰ36257 the executionВҰ36259 pole,
\v 22 andВҰ36261 so theyВҰ36263 all arrived at GolgothaВҰ36268 (whichВҰ36270 means вҖҳPlaceВҰ36275 of the skullВҰ36275вҖҷ).
\v 23 There the soldiers went to give some spiced wine to Yeshua, butВҰ36286 heВҰ36288 declined it.
\v 24 \x + \xo 15:24: \xt Psa 22:18.\x*SoВҰ36289 theyВҰ36294 carried out the executionВҰ36290, taking Yeshua's clothesВҰ36297 andВҰ36304 drawing straws to see who would get what.
\v 25 By now itВҰ36307 was around 9am, andВҰ36312 theyВҰ36314 affixed Yeshua to the pole.
\v 26 The chargeВҰ36322 had been written out andВҰ36316 attached \add at the top\add*: вҖңThe kingВҰ36328 of the Jews.вҖқ
\v 27 That morning, twoВҰ36337 thieves were also executedВҰ36334 thereвҖ”one on each side of Yeshua.
\p
\v 28 в—ҳ
\v 29 \x + \xo 15:29: a \xt Psa 22:7; 109:25; \xo b \xt Yhn 2:19; Mrk 14:58.\x*As people passed by on the path, they insulted Yeshua, shakingВҰ36365 theirВҰ36368 headsВҰ36367 and shouting, вҖңHoy there! You who reckoned youВҰ36373 could demolish the templeВҰ36376 and rebuild itВҰ36378 in threeВҰ36380 daysВҰ36381,
\v 30 comeВҰ36387 down from that pole and saveВҰ36383 yourselfВҰ36384.вҖқ
\p
\v 31 SimilarlyВҰ36391 the chiefВҰ36395 priestsВҰ36395 and the religiousВҰ36402 teachersВҰ36402 laughed together and mocked, вҖңHe did miracles for othersВҰ36404, but he can'tВҰ36407 even saveВҰ36409 himselfВҰ36406.
\v 32 The so-called вҖҳ\nd chosenВҰ36411\nd* oneвҖҷ or вҖҳkingВҰ36413 of YisraelвҖҷ. Now, if he'd just comeВҰ36416 down from there, thenВҰ36427 we'd be able to believeВҰ36425 him.вҖқ
\p Even the other two being executedВҰ36429 with him were deridingВҰ36432 him.
\s1 Yeshua breathes his last
\rem /s1 The Death of Jesus
\r (Yhn 19:28-30; Mat. 27:45-56; Luke 23:44-49)
\p
\v 33 At noon, it got dark everywhere, untilВҰ36448 around 3pm,
\v 34 \x + \xo 15:34: \xt Psa 22:1.\x*when \nd Yeshua\nd* shoutedВҰ36458 loudlyВҰ36462, вҖң\wj MyВҰ36475 god, myВҰ36475 god, why have you abandonedВҰ36482 me?\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 35 Some of the people standing nearby thought he was callingВҰ36497 the prophet Eliyah \add (ElijahВҰ36496)\add*.
\v 36 \x + \xo 15:36: \xt Psa 69:21.\x*One of them ran, and soaked a spongeВҰ36507 in some sour wine, thenВҰ36501 put it on a stick and held it up for Yeshua to drinkВҰ36513, sayingВҰ36515, вҖңHang on. Let's seeВҰ36519 if Eliyah does come to get him down.вҖқ
\p
\v 37 ButВҰ36526 just thenВҰ36526 \nd YeshuaВҰ36527\nd* uttered a loudВҰ36530 cryВҰ36529 andВҰ36526 exhaled his last breath.
\p
\v 38 \x + \xo 15:38: \xt Exo 26:31-33.\x*(Back in the templeВҰ36536, the curtainВҰ36534 tore down the middle from the top to the bottomВҰ36545.)
\v 39 WhenВҰ36547 Yeshua died, the Roman centurionВҰ36549 who had been standing back watching everything saidВҰ36564, вҖңThis manВҰ36568 was definitely God's son.вҖқ
\p
\v 40 \x + \xo 15:40-41: \xt Luk 8:2-3.\x*Further back, there was also a group of womenВҰ36579 observingВҰ36582 everything. These included Maria from MagdalaВҰ36589, Maria the motherВҰ36600 of young Yacob and Yoses, and SalomeВҰ36602,
\v 41 and others who had followedВҰ36610 Yeshua around GalileeВҰ36609 and helped look afterВҰ36612 him, along with many others who had comeВҰ36622 down with him to Yerushalem.
\s1 Yosef boldly lays the body in a burial chamber
\rem /s1 The Burial of Jesus
\r (Yhn 19:38-42; Mat. 27:57-61; Luke 23:50-56)
\p
\v 42 As eveningВҰ36628 came, it was now the Preparation Day, i.e., the day before the Rest Day.
\v 43 Yosef (who'd comeВҰ36641 from the city of ArimatheaВҰ36646 and one who was waitingВҰ36654 for the coming of God's kingdomВҰ36656), a prominentВҰ36647 councilВҰ36648 memberВҰ36648, steeled himselfВҰ36652 up and wentВҰ36661 in to see the governor to get permission to transfer \nd Yeshua's\nd* bodyВҰ36669.
\v 44 Governor PilateВҰ36674 didn't think he'd be dead yet, so he calledВҰ36683 an army commander to find out if Yeshua had indeed died.
\v 45 As soon as he found out, he gave Yosef permission,
\v 46 so Yosef \add and his companions\add* went and boughtВҰ36713 some linen burial cloth and thenВҰ36710, removing Yeshua's body from the pole, wrappedВҰ36721 it in the cloth and placedВҰ36729 it in a burial chamber thatВҰ36737 had been chiselled into a rockface. ThenВҰ36710 they rolledВҰ36744 a rockВҰ36742 across the opening.
\v 47 Others were watching and noted whereВҰ36772 the body had been laid, includingВҰ36760 Maria from MagdalaВҰ36759 and Maria who was Yoses' motherВҰ36762.
\c 16
\s1 The massive shock at the burial chamber
\rem /s1 The Resurrection of Jesus
\r (Yhn 20:1-10; Mat. 28:1-8; Luke 24:1-12)
\p
\v 1 After the Rest Day was over, Maria from MagdalaВҰ36783 and Maria the motherВҰ36786 of Yacob and SalomeВҰ36790, went and boughtВҰ36792 some traditional burial spicesВҰ36793 that evening to take to the burial chamber and place with the body.
\v 2 ThenВҰ36800 very earlyВҰ36803 on Sunday morning theyВҰ36811 went to the chamber, arriving just as the sunВҰ36820 was rising.
\v 3 ButВҰ36821 they realised that they didn't have anyone with them to roll the rockВҰ36835 away that was covering the entrance.
\v 4 However, when they lookedВҰ36847 they saw that the very largeВҰ36863 rockВҰ36860 had already been rolledВҰ36854 away.
\v 5 SoВҰ36866 they went on into the burial chamber andВҰ36866 were totally stunned to find a youngВҰ36874 manВҰ36874 dressed in whiteВҰ36882, sittingВҰ36876 in there on the side.
\p
\v 6 He assured them, вҖңDon'tВҰ36894 be surprised. I know you're lookingВҰ36902 forВҰ36902 \nd Yeshua\nd* from \nd NazarethВҰ36904\nd*, the one who was executedВҰ36907 on a pole. ButВҰ36888 seeВҰ36912 there whereВҰ36920 his body wasвҖ”he's not there because he came back to life.
\v 7 \x + \xo 16:7: \xt Mat 26:32; Mrk 14:28.\x*So you three should go and tell hisВҰ36929 apprenticesВҰ36928, and PeterВҰ36932 in particular, that he's going to go up ahead of them to GalileeВҰ36940 and you'll all see him up thereВҰ36941, just as he already told you.вҖқ
\p
\v 8 SoВҰ36949 they left the chamber and took off running, still stunned and shaking and too scared to stop and to talk to anyoneВҰ36969.
\rem It's not certain whether or not the following longer ending of this document was actually penned by the same author (Mark), or whether it was appended slightly later. Expert scholars are divided on this, and hence it's included here for your consideration:
\s1 \add The others don't believe that Maria saw Yeshua\add*
\rem /s1 AN OLD ENDING TO THE GOSPEL; THE LONGER ENDING OF MARK; Jesus Appears to Mary Magdalene
\r (Yhn 20:11-18; Mat. 28:9-10)
\rem /s2 [The most reliable early manuscripts and other ancient witnesses do not have Mark 16.9-20.]
\p
\v 9 \add After coming back to life early on Sunday morning, Yeshua appeared first to Maria from Magdala. (She was the one that he had once commanded seven demons to leave.)\add*
\v 10 \add After leaving him, she went and told his followers who were mourning and weeping at his loss.\add*
\v 11 \add But when she told them that he is alive again and that she'd seen him, they simply didn't believe her.\add*
\s1 \add Yeshua appears to two of his followers\add*
\rem /s1 Jesus Appears to Two Disciples; Jesus Appears to Two Followers
\r (Luke 24:13-35)
\p
\v 12 \add Later on, Yeshua appeared in a different form to two of his followers on the path as they left Yerushalem and headed out to the countryside,\add*
\v 13 \add but when they hurried back and told the others, no one believed them.\add*
\s1 \add Yeshua appears to his apprentices and instructs them\add*
\rem /s1 Jesus Appears to the Eleven; Jesus Commissions the Disciples
\r (Yhn 20:19-23; Mat. 28:16-20; Luke 24:36-49; Acts 1:6-8)
\p
\v 14 \add Later again when the eleven apprentices were sitting around eating, Yeshua appeared in the room and scolded them for not believing and for being so stubborn when they hadn't believed others who had told them that he'd come back from the dead.\add*
\v 15 \add Then he instructed them, вҖң\+wj Travel around all the world\+wj*\add*\x + \xo 16:15: \xt Acts 1:8.\x* \add \+wj and tell everyone the good message.\+wj*\add*
\v 16 \add \+wj Anyone who believes and gets immersed in water will be saved, however, those who refuse to believe will be condemned to death.\+wj*\add*
\v 17 \add \+wj Those who believe will be able to do miracles: they'll be able to use my authority to command demons to leave and to speak new languages,\+wj*\add*
\v 18 \add \+wj and they'll be able to pick up snakes. If they drink anything poisonous, it won't hurt them, and they will place their hands on people and make them better.\+wj*вҖқ\add*
\s1 \add Yeshua is lifted up to heaven\add*
\rem /s1 The Ascension of Jesus; Jesus Is Taken Up to Heaven
\r (Luke 24:50-53; Acts 1:9-11)
\p
\v 19 \add When Yeshua had finished speaking, he was lifted up into heaven and seated in the honoured place\add*\x + \xo 16:19: \xt Acts 1:9-11.\x* \add next to God.\add*
\v 20 \add Then his followers went around preaching everywhere, and God worked through them and so they were able to confirm the truth of their preaching by doing miracles.\add*
